110/*
111 * The following actions directly effect the spa's sync-to-convergence logic.
112 * The values below define the sync pass when we start performing the action.
113 * Care should be taken when changing these values as they directly impact
114 * spa_sync() performance. Tuning these values may introduce subtle performance
115 * pathologies and should only be done in the context of performance analysis.
116 * These tunables will eventually be removed and replaced with #defines once
117 * enough analysis has been done to determine optimal values.
118 *
119 * The 'zfs_sync_pass_deferred_free' pass must be greater than 1 to ensure that
120 * regular blocks are not deferred.

150void
151zio_init(void)
152{
153 size_t c;
154 zio_cache = kmem_cache_create("zio_cache",
155 sizeof (zio_t), 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0);
156 zio_link_cache = kmem_cache_create("zio_link_cache",
157 sizeof (zio_link_t), 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0);
158
159#ifndef __NetBSD__
160 if (!zio_use_uma)
161 goto out;
162
163 /*
164 * For small buffers, we want a cache for each multiple of
165 * SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE. For larger buffers, we want a cache
166 * for each quarter-power of 2.
167 */
168 for (c = 0; c < SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT; c++) {
169 size_t size = (c + 1) << SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT;
170 size_t p2 = size;
171 size_t align = 0;
172 int cflags = zio_exclude_metadata ? KMC_NODEBUG : 0;
173
174 while (!ISP2(p2))
175 p2 &= p2 - 1;
176
177#ifdef illumos
178#ifndef _KERNEL
179 /*
180 * If we are using watchpoints, put each buffer on its own page,
181 * to eliminate the performance overhead of trapping to the
182 * kernel when modifying a non-watched buffer that shares the
183 * page with a watched buffer.
184 */
185 if (arc_watch && !IS_P2ALIGNED(size, PAGESIZE))
186 continue;
187#endif
188#endif /* illumos */
189 if (size <= 4 * SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE) {
190 align = SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE;
191 } else if (IS_P2ALIGNED(size, p2 >> 2)) {
192 align = MIN(p2 >> 2, PAGESIZE);
193 }
194
195 if (align != 0) {
196 char name[36];
197 (void) sprintf(name, "zio_buf_%lu", (ulong_t)size);
198 zio_buf_cache[c] = kmem_cache_create(name, size,
199 align, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, cflags);
200
201 /*
202 * Since zio_data bufs do not appear in crash dumps, we
203 * pass KMC_NOTOUCH so that no allocator metadata is
204 * stored with the buffers.
205 */
206 (void) sprintf(name, "zio_data_buf_%lu", (ulong_t)size);
207 zio_data_buf_cache[c] = kmem_cache_create(name, size,
208 align, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,
209 cflags | KMC_NOTOUCH | KMC_NODEBUG);
210 }
211 }
212
213 while (--c != 0) {
214 ASSERT(zio_buf_cache[c] != NULL);
215 if (zio_buf_cache[c - 1] == NULL)
216 zio_buf_cache[c - 1] = zio_buf_cache[c];
217
218 ASSERT(zio_data_buf_cache[c] != NULL);
219 if (zio_data_buf_cache[c - 1] == NULL)
220 zio_data_buf_cache[c - 1] = zio_data_buf_cache[c];
221 }
222out:
223#endif /* __NetBSD__ */
224
225 zio_inject_init();
226
227 zio_trim_ksp = kstat_create("zfs", 0, "zio_trim", "misc",
228 KSTAT_TYPE_NAMED,
229 sizeof(zio_trim_stats) / sizeof(kstat_named_t),
230 KSTAT_FLAG_VIRTUAL);
231
232 if (zio_trim_ksp != NULL) {
233 zio_trim_ksp->ks_data = &zio_trim_stats;
234 kstat_install(zio_trim_ksp);
235 }
236}
237
238void
239zio_fini(void)
240{
241 size_t c;
242 kmem_cache_t *last_cache = NULL;
243 kmem_cache_t *last_data_cache = NULL;
244
245#ifndef __NetBSD__
246 for (c = 0; c < SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT; c++) {
247 if (zio_buf_cache[c] != last_cache) {
248 last_cache = zio_buf_cache[c];
249 kmem_cache_destroy(zio_buf_cache[c]);
250 }
251 zio_buf_cache[c] = NULL;
252
253 if (zio_data_buf_cache[c] != last_data_cache) {
254 last_data_cache = zio_data_buf_cache[c];
255 kmem_cache_destroy(zio_data_buf_cache[c]);
256 }
257 zio_data_buf_cache[c] = NULL;
258 }
259#endif /* __NetBSD__ */
260
261 kmem_cache_destroy(zio_link_cache);
262 kmem_cache_destroy(zio_cache);
263
264 zio_inject_fini();
265
266 if (zio_trim_ksp != NULL) {
267 kstat_delete(zio_trim_ksp);
268 zio_trim_ksp = NULL;
269 }
270}

272/*
273 * ==========================================================================
274 * Allocate and free I/O buffers
275 * ==========================================================================
276 */
277
278/*
279 * Use zio_buf_alloc to allocate ZFS metadata. This data will appear in a
280 * crashdump if the kernel panics, so use it judiciously. Obviously, it's
281 * useful to inspect ZFS metadata, but if possible, we should avoid keeping
282 * excess / transient data in-core during a crashdump.
283 */
284static void *
285zio_buf_alloc_impl(size_t size, boolean_t canwait)
286{
287 size_t c = (size - 1) >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT;
288 int flags = zio_exclude_metadata ? KM_NODEBUG : 0;
289
290 VERIFY3U(c, <, SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT);
291
292 if (zio_use_uma) {
293 return (kmem_cache_alloc(zio_buf_cache[c],
294 canwait ? KM_PUSHPAGE : KM_NOSLEEP));
295 } else {
296 return (kmem_alloc(size,
297 (canwait ? KM_SLEEP : KM_NOSLEEP) | flags));
298 }
299}
300
301void *
302zio_buf_alloc(size_t size)
303{
304 return (zio_buf_alloc_impl(size, B_TRUE));
305}
306
307void *
308zio_buf_alloc_nowait(size_t size)
309{
310 return (zio_buf_alloc_impl(size, B_FALSE));
311}
312
313/*
314 * Use zio_data_buf_alloc to allocate data. The data will not appear in a
315 * crashdump if the kernel panics. This exists so that we will limit the amount
316 * of ZFS data that shows up in a kernel crashdump. (Thus reducing the amount
317 * of kernel heap dumped to disk when the kernel panics)
318 */
319void *
320zio_data_buf_alloc(size_t size)
321{
322 size_t c = (size - 1) >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT;
323
324 VERIFY3U(c, <, SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT);
325
326 if (zio_use_uma)
327 return (kmem_cache_alloc(zio_data_buf_cache[c], KM_PUSHPAGE));
328 else
329 return (kmem_alloc(size, KM_SLEEP | KM_NODEBUG));
330}
331
332void
333zio_buf_free(void *buf, size_t size)
334{
335 size_t c = (size - 1) >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT;
336
337 VERIFY3U(c, <, SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT);
338
339 if (zio_use_uma)
340 kmem_cache_free(zio_buf_cache[c], buf);
341 else
342 kmem_free(buf, size);
343}
344
345void
346zio_data_buf_free(void *buf, size_t size)
347{
348 size_t c = (size - 1) >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT;
349
350 VERIFY3U(c, <, SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE >> SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT);
351
352 if (zio_use_uma)
353 kmem_cache_free(zio_data_buf_cache[c], buf);
354 else
355 kmem_free(buf, size);
356}

358/*
359 * ==========================================================================
360 * Push and pop I/O transform buffers
361 * ==========================================================================
362 */
363void
364zio_push_transform(zio_t *zio, void *data, uint64_t size, uint64_t bufsize,
365 zio_transform_func_t *transform)
366{
367 zio_transform_t *zt = kmem_alloc(sizeof (zio_transform_t), KM_SLEEP);
368
369 zt->zt_orig_data = zio->io_data;
370 zt->zt_orig_size = zio->io_size;
371 zt->zt_bufsize = bufsize;
372 zt->zt_transform = transform;
373
374 zt->zt_next = zio->io_transform_stack;
375 zio->io_transform_stack = zt;
376
377 zio->io_data = data;
378 zio->io_size = size;
379}
380
381void
382zio_pop_transforms(zio_t *zio)
383{
384 zio_transform_t *zt;
385
386 while ((zt = zio->io_transform_stack) != NULL) {
387 if (zt->zt_transform != NULL)
388 zt->zt_transform(zio,
389 zt->zt_orig_data, zt->zt_orig_size);
390
391 if (zt->zt_bufsize != 0)
392 zio_buf_free(zio->io_data, zt->zt_bufsize);
393
394 zio->io_data = zt->zt_orig_data;
395 zio->io_size = zt->zt_orig_size;
396 zio->io_transform_stack = zt->zt_next;
397
398 kmem_free(zt, sizeof (zio_transform_t));
399 }
400}

407static void
408zio_subblock(zio_t *zio, void *data, uint64_t size)
409{
410 ASSERT(zio->io_size > size);
411
412 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ)
413 bcopy(zio->io_data, data, size);
414}
415
416static void
417zio_decompress(zio_t *zio, void *data, uint64_t size)
418{
419 if (zio->io_error == 0 &&
420 zio_decompress_data(BP_GET_COMPRESS(zio->io_bp),
421 zio->io_data, data, zio->io_size, size) != 0)
422 zio->io_error = SET_ERROR(EIO);
423}

425/*
426 * ==========================================================================
427 * I/O parent/child relationships and pipeline interlocks
428 * ==========================================================================
429 */
430zio_t *
431zio_walk_parents(zio_t *cio, zio_link_t **zl)
432{
433 list_t *pl = &cio->io_parent_list;
434
435 *zl = (*zl == NULL) ? list_head(pl) : list_next(pl, *zl);
436 if (*zl == NULL)
437 return (NULL);
438
439 ASSERT((*zl)->zl_child == cio);
440 return ((*zl)->zl_parent);
441}
442
443zio_t *
444zio_walk_children(zio_t *pio, zio_link_t **zl)
445{
446 list_t *cl = &pio->io_child_list;
447
448 *zl = (*zl == NULL) ? list_head(cl) : list_next(cl, *zl);
449 if (*zl == NULL)
450 return (NULL);
451
452 ASSERT((*zl)->zl_parent == pio);
453 return ((*zl)->zl_child);
454}
455
456zio_t *
457zio_unique_parent(zio_t *cio)
458{
459 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
460 zio_t *pio = zio_walk_parents(cio, &zl);
461
462 VERIFY3P(zio_walk_parents(cio, &zl), ==, NULL);
463 return (pio);
464}
465
466void
467zio_add_child(zio_t *pio, zio_t *cio)
468{
469 zio_link_t *zl = kmem_cache_alloc(zio_link_cache, KM_SLEEP);
470
471 /*
472 * Logical I/Os can have logical, gang, or vdev children.
473 * Gang I/Os can have gang or vdev children.
474 * Vdev I/Os can only have vdev children.
475 * The following ASSERT captures all of these constraints.
476 */
477 ASSERT(cio->io_child_type <= pio->io_child_type);
478
479 zl->zl_parent = pio;
480 zl->zl_child = cio;
481
482 mutex_enter(&cio->io_lock);
483 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
484
485 ASSERT(pio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_DONE] == 0);
486
487 for (int w = 0; w < ZIO_WAIT_TYPES; w++)
488 pio->io_children[cio->io_child_type][w] += !cio->io_state[w];
489
490 list_insert_head(&pio->io_child_list, zl);
491 list_insert_head(&cio->io_parent_list, zl);
492
493 pio->io_child_count++;
494 cio->io_parent_count++;
495
496 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
497 mutex_exit(&cio->io_lock);
498}
499
500static void
501zio_remove_child(zio_t *pio, zio_t *cio, zio_link_t *zl)
502{
503 ASSERT(zl->zl_parent == pio);
504 ASSERT(zl->zl_child == cio);
505
506 mutex_enter(&cio->io_lock);
507 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
508
509 list_remove(&pio->io_child_list, zl);
510 list_remove(&cio->io_parent_list, zl);
511
512 pio->io_child_count--;
513 cio->io_parent_count--;
514
515 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
516 mutex_exit(&cio->io_lock);
517
518 kmem_cache_free(zio_link_cache, zl);
519}
520
521static boolean_t
522zio_wait_for_children(zio_t *zio, enum zio_child child, enum zio_wait_type wait)
523{
524 uint64_t *countp = &zio->io_children[child][wait];
525 boolean_t waiting = B_FALSE;
526
527 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
528 ASSERT(zio->io_stall == NULL);
529 if (*countp != 0) {
530 zio->io_stage >>= 1;
531 ASSERT3U(zio->io_stage, !=, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN);
532 zio->io_stall = countp;
533 waiting = B_TRUE;
534 }
535 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
536
537 return (waiting);
538}
539
540static void
541zio_notify_parent(zio_t *pio, zio_t *zio, enum zio_wait_type wait)
542{
543 uint64_t *countp = &pio->io_children[zio->io_child_type][wait];
544 int *errorp = &pio->io_child_error[zio->io_child_type];
545
546 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
547 if (zio->io_error && !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE))
548 *errorp = zio_worst_error(*errorp, zio->io_error);
549 pio->io_reexecute |= zio->io_reexecute;
550 ASSERT3U(*countp, >, 0);
551
552 (*countp)--;
553
554 if (*countp == 0 && pio->io_stall == countp) {
555 zio_taskq_type_t type =
556 pio->io_stage < ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START ? ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE :
557 ZIO_TASKQ_INTERRUPT;
558 pio->io_stall = NULL;
559 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
560 /*
561 * Dispatch the parent zio in its own taskq so that
562 * the child can continue to make progress. This also
563 * prevents overflowing the stack when we have deeply nested
564 * parent-child relationships.
565 */
566 zio_taskq_dispatch(pio, type, B_FALSE);
567 } else {
568 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
569 }
570}
571
572static void
573zio_inherit_child_errors(zio_t *zio, enum zio_child c)
574{
575 if (zio->io_child_error[c] != 0 && zio->io_error == 0)
576 zio->io_error = zio->io_child_error[c];
577}

579int
580zio_timestamp_compare(const void *x1, const void *x2)
581{
582 const zio_t *z1 = x1;
583 const zio_t *z2 = x2;
584
585 if (z1->io_queued_timestamp < z2->io_queued_timestamp)
586 return (-1);
587 if (z1->io_queued_timestamp > z2->io_queued_timestamp)
588 return (1);
589
590 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_objset < z2->io_bookmark.zb_objset)
591 return (-1);
592 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_objset > z2->io_bookmark.zb_objset)
593 return (1);
594
595 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_object < z2->io_bookmark.zb_object)
596 return (-1);
597 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_object > z2->io_bookmark.zb_object)
598 return (1);
599
600 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_level < z2->io_bookmark.zb_level)
601 return (-1);
602 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_level > z2->io_bookmark.zb_level)
603 return (1);
604
605 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_blkid < z2->io_bookmark.zb_blkid)
606 return (-1);
607 if (z1->io_bookmark.zb_blkid > z2->io_bookmark.zb_blkid)
608 return (1);
609
610 if (z1 < z2)
611 return (-1);
612 if (z1 > z2)
613 return (1);
614
615 return (0);
616}

618/*
619 * ==========================================================================
620 * Create the various types of I/O (read, write, free, etc)
621 * ==========================================================================
622 */
623static zio_t *
624zio_create(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, const blkptr_t *bp,
625 void *data, uint64_t size, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
626 zio_type_t type, zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags,
627 vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset, const zbookmark_phys_t *zb,
628 enum zio_stage stage, enum zio_stage pipeline)
629{
630 zio_t *zio;
631
632 ASSERT3U(type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE || size, <=, SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE);
633 ASSERT(P2PHASE(size, SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE) == 0);
634 ASSERT(P2PHASE(offset, SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE) == 0);
635
636 ASSERT(!vd || spa_config_held(spa, SCL_STATE_ALL, RW_READER));
637 ASSERT(!bp || !(flags & ZIO_FLAG_CONFIG_WRITER));
638 ASSERT(vd || stage == ZIO_STAGE_OPEN);
639
640 zio = kmem_cache_alloc(zio_cache, KM_SLEEP);
641 bzero(zio, sizeof (zio_t));
642
643 mutex_init(&zio->io_lock, NULL, MUTEX_DEFAULT, NULL);
644 cv_init(&zio->io_cv, NULL, CV_DEFAULT, NULL);
645
646 list_create(&zio->io_parent_list, sizeof (zio_link_t),
647 offsetof(zio_link_t, zl_parent_node));
648 list_create(&zio->io_child_list, sizeof (zio_link_t),
649 offsetof(zio_link_t, zl_child_node));
650 metaslab_trace_init(&zio->io_alloc_list);
651
652 if (vd != NULL)
653 zio->io_child_type = ZIO_CHILD_VDEV;
654 else if (flags & ZIO_FLAG_GANG_CHILD)
655 zio->io_child_type = ZIO_CHILD_GANG;
656 else if (flags & ZIO_FLAG_DDT_CHILD)
657 zio->io_child_type = ZIO_CHILD_DDT;
658 else
659 zio->io_child_type = ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL;
660
661 if (bp != NULL) {
662 zio->io_bp = (blkptr_t *)bp;
663 zio->io_bp_copy = *bp;
664 zio->io_bp_orig = *bp;
665 if (type != ZIO_TYPE_WRITE ||
666 zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_DDT)
667 zio->io_bp = &zio->io_bp_copy; /* so caller can free */
668 if (zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL)
669 zio->io_logical = zio;
670 if (zio->io_child_type > ZIO_CHILD_GANG && BP_IS_GANG(bp))
671 pipeline |= ZIO_GANG_STAGES;
672 }
673
674 zio->io_spa = spa;
675 zio->io_txg = txg;
676 zio->io_done = done;
677 zio->io_private = private;
678 zio->io_type = type;
679 zio->io_priority = priority;
680 zio->io_vd = vd;
681 zio->io_offset = offset;
682 zio->io_orig_data = zio->io_data = data;
683 zio->io_orig_size = zio->io_size = size;
684 zio->io_orig_flags = zio->io_flags = flags;
685 zio->io_orig_stage = zio->io_stage = stage;
686 zio->io_orig_pipeline = zio->io_pipeline = pipeline;
687 zio->io_pipeline_trace = ZIO_STAGE_OPEN;
688
689 zio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_READY] = (stage >= ZIO_STAGE_READY);
690 zio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_DONE] = (stage >= ZIO_STAGE_DONE);
691
692 if (zb != NULL)
693 zio->io_bookmark = *zb;
694
695 if (pio != NULL) {
696 if (zio->io_logical == NULL)
697 zio->io_logical = pio->io_logical;
698 if (zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG)
699 zio->io_gang_leader = pio->io_gang_leader;
700 zio_add_child(pio, zio);
701 }
702
703 return (zio);
704}
705
706static void
707zio_destroy(zio_t *zio)
708{
709 metaslab_trace_fini(&zio->io_alloc_list);
710 list_destroy(&zio->io_parent_list);
711 list_destroy(&zio->io_child_list);
712 mutex_destroy(&zio->io_lock);
713 cv_destroy(&zio->io_cv);
714 kmem_cache_free(zio_cache, zio);
715}

735
736void
737zfs_blkptr_verify(spa_t *spa, const blkptr_t *bp)
738{
739 if (!DMU_OT_IS_VALID(BP_GET_TYPE(bp))) {
740 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid TYPE %llu",
741 bp, (longlong_t)BP_GET_TYPE(bp));
742 }
743 if (BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) >= ZIO_CHECKSUM_FUNCTIONS ||
744 BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) <= ZIO_CHECKSUM_ON) {
745 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid CHECKSUM %llu",
746 bp, (longlong_t)BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp));
747 }
748 if (BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp) >= ZIO_COMPRESS_FUNCTIONS ||
749 BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp) <= ZIO_COMPRESS_ON) {
750 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid COMPRESS %llu",
751 bp, (longlong_t)BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp));
752 }
753 if (BP_GET_LSIZE(bp) > SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE) {
754 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid LSIZE %llu",
755 bp, (longlong_t)BP_GET_LSIZE(bp));
756 }
757 if (BP_GET_PSIZE(bp) > SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE) {
758 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid PSIZE %llu",
759 bp, (longlong_t)BP_GET_PSIZE(bp));
760 }
761
762 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp)) {
763 if (BPE_GET_ETYPE(bp) > NUM_BP_EMBEDDED_TYPES) {
764 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p has invalid ETYPE %llu",
765 bp, (longlong_t)BPE_GET_ETYPE(bp));
766 }
767 }
768
769 /*
770 * Pool-specific checks.
771 *
772 * Note: it would be nice to verify that the blk_birth and
773 * BP_PHYSICAL_BIRTH() are not too large. However, spa_freeze()
774 * allows the birth time of log blocks (and dmu_sync()-ed blocks
775 * that are in the log) to be arbitrarily large.
776 */
777 for (int i = 0; i < BP_GET_NDVAS(bp); i++) {
778 uint64_t vdevid = DVA_GET_VDEV(&bp->blk_dva[i]);
779 if (vdevid >= spa->spa_root_vdev->vdev_children) {
780 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p DVA %u has invalid "
781 "VDEV %llu",
782 bp, i, (longlong_t)vdevid);
783 continue;
784 }
785 vdev_t *vd = spa->spa_root_vdev->vdev_child[vdevid];
786 if (vd == NULL) {
787 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p DVA %u has invalid "
788 "VDEV %llu",
789 bp, i, (longlong_t)vdevid);
790 continue;
791 }
792 if (vd->vdev_ops == &vdev_hole_ops) {
793 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p DVA %u has hole "
794 "VDEV %llu",
795 bp, i, (longlong_t)vdevid);
796 continue;
797 }
798 if (vd->vdev_ops == &vdev_missing_ops) {
799 /*
800 * "missing" vdevs are valid during import, but we
801 * don't have their detailed info (e.g. asize), so
802 * we can't perform any more checks on them.
803 */
804 continue;
805 }
806 uint64_t offset = DVA_GET_OFFSET(&bp->blk_dva[i]);
807 uint64_t asize = DVA_GET_ASIZE(&bp->blk_dva[i]);
808 if (BP_IS_GANG(bp))
809 asize = vdev_psize_to_asize(vd, SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE);
810 if (offset + asize > vd->vdev_asize) {
811 zfs_panic_recover("blkptr at %p DVA %u has invalid "
812 "OFFSET %llu",
813 bp, i, (longlong_t)offset);
814 }
815 }
816}
817
818zio_t *
819zio_read(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, const blkptr_t *bp,
820 void *data, uint64_t size, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
821 zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags, const zbookmark_phys_t *zb)
822{
823 zio_t *zio;
824
825 zfs_blkptr_verify(spa, bp);
826
827 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, BP_PHYSICAL_BIRTH(bp), bp,
828 data, size, done, private,
829 ZIO_TYPE_READ, priority, flags, NULL, 0, zb,
830 ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, (flags & ZIO_FLAG_DDT_CHILD) ?
831 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_READ_PIPELINE : ZIO_READ_PIPELINE);
832
833 return (zio);
834}
835
836zio_t *
837zio_write(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, blkptr_t *bp,
838 void *data, uint64_t size, const zio_prop_t *zp,
839 zio_done_func_t *ready, zio_done_func_t *children_ready,
840 zio_done_func_t *physdone, zio_done_func_t *done,
841 void *private, zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags,
842 const zbookmark_phys_t *zb)
843{
844 zio_t *zio;
845
846 ASSERT(zp->zp_checksum >= ZIO_CHECKSUM_OFF &&
847 zp->zp_checksum < ZIO_CHECKSUM_FUNCTIONS &&
848 zp->zp_compress >= ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF &&
849 zp->zp_compress < ZIO_COMPRESS_FUNCTIONS &&
850 DMU_OT_IS_VALID(zp->zp_type) &&
851 zp->zp_level < 32 &&
852 zp->zp_copies > 0 &&
853 zp->zp_copies <= spa_max_replication(spa));
854
855 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, txg, bp, data, size, done, private,
856 ZIO_TYPE_WRITE, priority, flags, NULL, 0, zb,
857 ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, (flags & ZIO_FLAG_DDT_CHILD) ?
858 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_WRITE_PIPELINE : ZIO_WRITE_PIPELINE);
859
860 zio->io_ready = ready;
861 zio->io_children_ready = children_ready;
862 zio->io_physdone = physdone;
863 zio->io_prop = *zp;
864
865 /*
866 * Data can be NULL if we are going to call zio_write_override() to
867 * provide the already-allocated BP. But we may need the data to
868 * verify a dedup hit (if requested). In this case, don't try to
869 * dedup (just take the already-allocated BP verbatim).
870 */
871 if (data == NULL && zio->io_prop.zp_dedup_verify) {
872 zio->io_prop.zp_dedup = zio->io_prop.zp_dedup_verify = B_FALSE;
873 }
874
875 return (zio);
876}

878zio_t *
879zio_rewrite(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, blkptr_t *bp, void *data,
880 uint64_t size, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
881 zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags, zbookmark_phys_t *zb)
882{
883 zio_t *zio;
884
885 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, txg, bp, data, size, done, private,
886 ZIO_TYPE_WRITE, priority, flags | ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE, NULL, 0, zb,
887 ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_REWRITE_PIPELINE);
888
889 return (zio);
890}
891
892void
893zio_write_override(zio_t *zio, blkptr_t *bp, int copies, boolean_t nopwrite)
894{
895 ASSERT(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
896 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
897 ASSERT(zio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_OPEN);
898 ASSERT(zio->io_txg == spa_syncing_txg(zio->io_spa));
899
900 /*
901 * We must reset the io_prop to match the values that existed
902 * when the bp was first written by dmu_sync() keeping in mind
903 * that nopwrite and dedup are mutually exclusive.
904 */
905 zio->io_prop.zp_dedup = nopwrite ? B_FALSE : zio->io_prop.zp_dedup;
906 zio->io_prop.zp_nopwrite = nopwrite;
907 zio->io_prop.zp_copies = copies;
908 zio->io_bp_override = bp;
909}
910
911void
912zio_free(spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, const blkptr_t *bp)
913{
914
915 /*
916 * The check for EMBEDDED is a performance optimization. We
917 * process the free here (by ignoring it) rather than
918 * putting it on the list and then processing it in zio_free_sync().
919 */
920 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp))
921 return;
922 metaslab_check_free(spa, bp);
923
924 /*
925 * Frees that are for the currently-syncing txg, are not going to be
926 * deferred, and which will not need to do a read (i.e. not GANG or
927 * DEDUP), can be processed immediately. Otherwise, put them on the
928 * in-memory list for later processing.
929 */
930 if (zfs_trim_enabled || BP_IS_GANG(bp) || BP_GET_DEDUP(bp) ||
931 txg != spa->spa_syncing_txg ||
932 spa_sync_pass(spa) >= zfs_sync_pass_deferred_free) {
933 bplist_append(&spa->spa_free_bplist[txg & TXG_MASK], bp);
934 } else {
935 VERIFY0(zio_wait(zio_free_sync(NULL, spa, txg, bp,
936 BP_GET_PSIZE(bp), 0)));
937 }
938}
939
940zio_t *
941zio_free_sync(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, const blkptr_t *bp,
942 uint64_t size, enum zio_flag flags)
943{
944 zio_t *zio;
945 enum zio_stage stage = ZIO_FREE_PIPELINE;
946
947 ASSERT(!BP_IS_HOLE(bp));
948 ASSERT(spa_syncing_txg(spa) == txg);
949 ASSERT(spa_sync_pass(spa) < zfs_sync_pass_deferred_free);
950
951 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp))
952 return (zio_null(pio, spa, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0));
953
954 metaslab_check_free(spa, bp);
955 arc_freed(spa, bp);
956
957 if (zfs_trim_enabled)
958 stage |= ZIO_STAGE_ISSUE_ASYNC | ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START |
959 ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_ASSESS;
960 /*
961 * GANG and DEDUP blocks can induce a read (for the gang block header,
962 * or the DDT), so issue them asynchronously so that this thread is
963 * not tied up.
964 */
965 else if (BP_IS_GANG(bp) || BP_GET_DEDUP(bp))
966 stage |= ZIO_STAGE_ISSUE_ASYNC;
967
968 flags |= ZIO_FLAG_DONT_QUEUE;
969
970 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, txg, bp, NULL, size,
971 NULL, NULL, ZIO_TYPE_FREE, ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW, flags,
972 NULL, 0, NULL, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, stage);
973
974 return (zio);
975}
976
977zio_t *
978zio_claim(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, uint64_t txg, const blkptr_t *bp,
979 zio_done_func_t *done, void *private, enum zio_flag flags)
980{
981 zio_t *zio;
982
983 dprintf_bp(bp, "claiming in txg %llu", txg);
984
985 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp))
986 return (zio_null(pio, spa, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0));
987
988 /*
989 * A claim is an allocation of a specific block. Claims are needed
990 * to support immediate writes in the intent log. The issue is that
991 * immediate writes contain committed data, but in a txg that was
992 * *not* committed. Upon opening the pool after an unclean shutdown,
993 * the intent log claims all blocks that contain immediate write data
994 * so that the SPA knows they're in use.
995 *
996 * All claims *must* be resolved in the first txg -- before the SPA
997 * starts allocating blocks -- so that nothing is allocated twice.
998 * If txg == 0 we just verify that the block is claimable.
999 */
1000 ASSERT3U(spa->spa_uberblock.ub_rootbp.blk_birth, <, spa_first_txg(spa));
1001 ASSERT(txg == spa_first_txg(spa) || txg == 0);
1002 ASSERT(!BP_GET_DEDUP(bp) || !spa_writeable(spa)); /* zdb(1M) */
1003
1004 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, txg, bp, NULL, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp),
1005 done, private, ZIO_TYPE_CLAIM, ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW, flags,
1006 NULL, 0, NULL, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_CLAIM_PIPELINE);
1007 ASSERT0(zio->io_queued_timestamp);
1008
1009 return (zio);
1010}
1011
1012zio_t *
1013zio_ioctl(zio_t *pio, spa_t *spa, vdev_t *vd, int cmd, uint64_t offset,
1014 uint64_t size, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
1015 zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags)
1016{
1017 zio_t *zio;
1018 int c;
1019
1020 if (vd->vdev_children == 0) {
1021 zio = zio_create(pio, spa, 0, NULL, NULL, size, done, private,
1022 ZIO_TYPE_IOCTL, priority, flags, vd, offset, NULL,
1023 ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_IOCTL_PIPELINE);
1024
1025 zio->io_cmd = cmd;
1026 } else {
1027 zio = zio_null(pio, spa, NULL, NULL, NULL, flags);
1028
1029 for (c = 0; c < vd->vdev_children; c++)
1030 zio_nowait(zio_ioctl(zio, spa, vd->vdev_child[c], cmd,
1031 offset, size, done, private, priority, flags));
1032 }
1033
1034 return (zio);
1035}

1037zio_t *
1038zio_read_phys(zio_t *pio, vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset, uint64_t size,
1039 void *data, int checksum, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
1040 zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags, boolean_t labels)
1041{
1042 zio_t *zio;
1043
1044 ASSERT(vd->vdev_children == 0);
1045 ASSERT(!labels || offset + size <= VDEV_LABEL_START_SIZE ||
1046 offset >= vd->vdev_psize - VDEV_LABEL_END_SIZE);
1047 ASSERT3U(offset + size, <=, vd->vdev_psize);
1048
1049 zio = zio_create(pio, vd->vdev_spa, 0, NULL, data, size, done, private,
1050 ZIO_TYPE_READ, priority, flags | ZIO_FLAG_PHYSICAL, vd, offset,
1051 NULL, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_READ_PHYS_PIPELINE);
1052
1053 zio->io_prop.zp_checksum = checksum;
1054
1055 return (zio);
1056}
1057
1058zio_t *
1059zio_write_phys(zio_t *pio, vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset, uint64_t size,
1060 void *data, int checksum, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private,
1061 zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags, boolean_t labels)
1062{
1063 zio_t *zio;
1064
1065 ASSERT(vd->vdev_children == 0);
1066 ASSERT(!labels || offset + size <= VDEV_LABEL_START_SIZE ||
1067 offset >= vd->vdev_psize - VDEV_LABEL_END_SIZE);
1068 ASSERT3U(offset + size, <=, vd->vdev_psize);
1069
1070 zio = zio_create(pio, vd->vdev_spa, 0, NULL, data, size, done, private,
1071 ZIO_TYPE_WRITE, priority, flags | ZIO_FLAG_PHYSICAL, vd, offset,
1072 NULL, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_WRITE_PHYS_PIPELINE);
1073
1074 zio->io_prop.zp_checksum = checksum;
1075
1076 if (zio_checksum_table[checksum].ci_flags & ZCHECKSUM_FLAG_EMBEDDED) {
1077 /*
1078 * zec checksums are necessarily destructive -- they modify
1079 * the end of the write buffer to hold the verifier/checksum.
1080 * Therefore, we must make a local copy in case the data is
1081 * being written to multiple places in parallel.
1082 */
1083 void *wbuf = zio_buf_alloc(size);
1084 bcopy(data, wbuf, size);
1085 zio_push_transform(zio, wbuf, size, size, NULL);
1086 }
1087
1088 return (zio);
1089}
1090
1091/*
1092 * Create a child I/O to do some work for us.
1093 */
1094zio_t *
1095zio_vdev_child_io(zio_t *pio, blkptr_t *bp, vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset,
1096 void *data, uint64_t size, int type, zio_priority_t priority,
1097 enum zio_flag flags, zio_done_func_t *done, void *private)
1098{
1099 enum zio_stage pipeline = ZIO_VDEV_CHILD_PIPELINE;
1100 zio_t *zio;
1101
1102 ASSERT(vd->vdev_parent ==
1103 (pio->io_vd ? pio->io_vd : pio->io_spa->spa_root_vdev));
1104
1105 if (type == ZIO_TYPE_READ && bp != NULL) {
1106 /*
1107 * If we have the bp, then the child should perform the
1108 * checksum and the parent need not. This pushes error
1109 * detection as close to the leaves as possible and
1110 * eliminates redundant checksums in the interior nodes.
1111 */
1112 pipeline |= ZIO_STAGE_CHECKSUM_VERIFY;
1113 pio->io_pipeline &= ~ZIO_STAGE_CHECKSUM_VERIFY;
1114 }
1115
1116 /* Not all IO types require vdev io done stage e.g. free */
1117 if (!(pio->io_pipeline & ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_DONE))
1118 pipeline &= ~ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_DONE;
1119
1120 if (vd->vdev_children == 0)
1121 offset += VDEV_LABEL_START_SIZE;
1122
1123 flags |= ZIO_VDEV_CHILD_FLAGS(pio) | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE;
1124
1125 /*
1126 * If we've decided to do a repair, the write is not speculative --
1127 * even if the original read was.
1128 */
1129 if (flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR)
1130 flags &= ~ZIO_FLAG_SPECULATIVE;
1131
1132 /*
1133 * If we're creating a child I/O that is not associated with a
1134 * top-level vdev, then the child zio is not an allocating I/O.
1135 * If this is a retried I/O then we ignore it since we will
1136 * have already processed the original allocating I/O.
1137 */
1138 if (flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING &&
1139 (vd != vd->vdev_top || (flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_RETRY))) {
1140 metaslab_class_t *mc = spa_normal_class(pio->io_spa);
1141
1142 ASSERT(mc->mc_alloc_throttle_enabled);
1143 ASSERT(type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
1144 ASSERT(priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
1145 ASSERT(!(flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR));
1146 ASSERT(!(pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE) ||
1147 pio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
1148
1149 flags &= ~ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING;
1150 }
1151
1152 zio = zio_create(pio, pio->io_spa, pio->io_txg, bp, data, size,
1153 done, private, type, priority, flags, vd, offset, &pio->io_bookmark,
1154 ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START >> 1, pipeline);
1155 ASSERT3U(zio->io_child_type, ==, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV);
1156
1157 zio->io_physdone = pio->io_physdone;
1158 if (vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf && zio->io_logical != NULL)
1159 zio->io_logical->io_phys_children++;
1160
1161 return (zio);
1162}
1163
1164zio_t *
1165zio_vdev_delegated_io(vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset, void *data, uint64_t size,
1166 int type, zio_priority_t priority, enum zio_flag flags,
1167 zio_done_func_t *done, void *private)
1168{
1169 zio_t *zio;
1170
1171 ASSERT(vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf);
1172
1173 zio = zio_create(NULL, vd->vdev_spa, 0, NULL,
1174 data, size, done, private, type, priority,
1175 flags | ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_RETRY | ZIO_FLAG_DELEGATED,
1176 vd, offset, NULL,
1177 ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START >> 1, ZIO_VDEV_CHILD_PIPELINE);
1178
1179 return (zio);
1180}
1181
1182void
1183zio_flush(zio_t *zio, vdev_t *vd)
1184{
1185 zio_nowait(zio_ioctl(zio, zio->io_spa, vd, DKIOCFLUSHWRITECACHE, 0, 0,
1186 NULL, NULL, ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW,
1187 ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_RETRY));
1188}
1189
1190zio_t *
1191zio_trim(zio_t *zio, spa_t *spa, vdev_t *vd, uint64_t offset, uint64_t size)
1192{
1193
1194 ASSERT(vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf);
1195
1196 return (zio_create(zio, spa, 0, NULL, NULL, size, NULL, NULL,
1197 ZIO_TYPE_FREE, ZIO_PRIORITY_TRIM, ZIO_FLAG_DONT_AGGREGATE |
1198 ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_RETRY,
1199 vd, offset, NULL, ZIO_STAGE_OPEN, ZIO_FREE_PHYS_PIPELINE));
1200}
1201
1202void
1203zio_shrink(zio_t *zio, uint64_t size)
1204{
1205 ASSERT(zio->io_executor == NULL);
1206 ASSERT(zio->io_orig_size == zio->io_size);
1207 ASSERT(size <= zio->io_size);
1208
1209 /*
1210 * We don't shrink for raidz because of problems with the
1211 * reconstruction when reading back less than the block size.
1212 * Note, BP_IS_RAIDZ() assumes no compression.
1213 */
1214 ASSERT(BP_GET_COMPRESS(zio->io_bp) == ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF);
1215 if (!BP_IS_RAIDZ(zio->io_bp))
1216 zio->io_orig_size = zio->io_size = size;
1217}
1218
1219/*
1220 * ==========================================================================
1221 * Prepare to read and write logical blocks
1222 * ==========================================================================
1223 */
1224
1225static int
1226zio_read_bp_init(zio_t *zio)
1227{
1228 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
1229
1230 if (BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp) != ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF &&
1231 zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL &&
1232 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_RAW)) {
1233 uint64_t psize =
1234 BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp) ? BPE_GET_PSIZE(bp) : BP_GET_PSIZE(bp);
1235 void *cbuf = zio_buf_alloc(psize);
1236
1237 zio_push_transform(zio, cbuf, psize, psize, zio_decompress);
1238 }
1239
1240 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp) && BPE_GET_ETYPE(bp) == BP_EMBEDDED_TYPE_DATA) {
1241 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
1242 decode_embedded_bp_compressed(bp, zio->io_data);
1243 } else {
1244 ASSERT(!BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp));
1245 }
1246
1247 if (!DMU_OT_IS_METADATA(BP_GET_TYPE(bp)) && BP_GET_LEVEL(bp) == 0)
1248 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_DONT_CACHE;
1249
1250 if (BP_GET_TYPE(bp) == DMU_OT_DDT_ZAP)
1251 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_DONT_CACHE;
1252
1253 if (BP_GET_DEDUP(bp) && zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL)
1254 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_DDT_READ_PIPELINE;
1255
1256 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1257}
1258
1259static int
1260zio_write_bp_init(zio_t *zio)
1261{
1262 if (!IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio))
1263 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1264
1265 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type != ZIO_CHILD_DDT);
1266
1267 if (zio->io_bp_override) {
1268 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
1269 zio_prop_t *zp = &zio->io_prop;
1270
1271 ASSERT(bp->blk_birth != zio->io_txg);
1272 ASSERT(BP_GET_DEDUP(zio->io_bp_override) == 0);
1273
1274 *bp = *zio->io_bp_override;
1275 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
1276
1277 if (BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp))
1278 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1279
1280 /*
1281 * If we've been overridden and nopwrite is set then
1282 * set the flag accordingly to indicate that a nopwrite
1283 * has already occurred.
1284 */
1285 if (!BP_IS_HOLE(bp) && zp->zp_nopwrite) {
1286 ASSERT(!zp->zp_dedup);
1287 ASSERT3U(BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp), ==, zp->zp_checksum);
1288 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE;
1289 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1290 }
1291
1292 ASSERT(!zp->zp_nopwrite);
1293
1294 if (BP_IS_HOLE(bp) || !zp->zp_dedup)
1295 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1296
1297 ASSERT((zio_checksum_table[zp->zp_checksum].ci_flags &
1298 ZCHECKSUM_FLAG_DEDUP) || zp->zp_dedup_verify);
1299
1300 if (BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) == zp->zp_checksum) {
1301 BP_SET_DEDUP(bp, 1);
1302 zio->io_pipeline |= ZIO_STAGE_DDT_WRITE;
1303 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1304 }
1305
1306 /*
1307 * We were unable to handle this as an override bp, treat
1308 * it as a regular write I/O.
1309 */
1310 zio->io_bp_override = NULL;
1311 *bp = zio->io_bp_orig;
1312 zio->io_pipeline = zio->io_orig_pipeline;
1313 }
1314
1315 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1316}
1317
1318static int
1319zio_write_compress(zio_t *zio)
1320{
1321 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
1322 zio_prop_t *zp = &zio->io_prop;
1323 enum zio_compress compress = zp->zp_compress;
1324 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
1325 uint64_t lsize = zio->io_size;
1326 uint64_t psize = lsize;
1327 int pass = 1;
1328
1329 /*
1330 * If our children haven't all reached the ready stage,
1331 * wait for them and then repeat this pipeline stage.
1332 */
1333 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_GANG, ZIO_WAIT_READY) ||
1334 zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL, ZIO_WAIT_READY))
1335 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
1336
1337 if (!IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio))
1338 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1339
1340 if (zio->io_children_ready != NULL) {
1341 /*
1342 * Now that all our children are ready, run the callback
1343 * associated with this zio in case it wants to modify the
1344 * data to be written.
1345 */
1346 ASSERT3U(zp->zp_level, >, 0);
1347 zio->io_children_ready(zio);
1348 }
1349
1350 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type != ZIO_CHILD_DDT);
1351 ASSERT(zio->io_bp_override == NULL);
1352
1353 if (!BP_IS_HOLE(bp) && bp->blk_birth == zio->io_txg) {
1354 /*
1355 * We're rewriting an existing block, which means we're
1356 * working on behalf of spa_sync(). For spa_sync() to
1357 * converge, it must eventually be the case that we don't
1358 * have to allocate new blocks. But compression changes
1359 * the blocksize, which forces a reallocate, and makes
1360 * convergence take longer. Therefore, after the first
1361 * few passes, stop compressing to ensure convergence.
1362 */
1363 pass = spa_sync_pass(spa);
1364
1365 ASSERT(zio->io_txg == spa_syncing_txg(spa));
1366 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
1367 ASSERT(!BP_GET_DEDUP(bp));
1368
1369 if (pass >= zfs_sync_pass_dont_compress)
1370 compress = ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF;
1371
1372 /* Make sure someone doesn't change their mind on overwrites */
1373 ASSERT(BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp) || MIN(zp->zp_copies + BP_IS_GANG(bp),
1374 spa_max_replication(spa)) == BP_GET_NDVAS(bp));
1375 }
1376
1377 if (compress != ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF) {
1378 void *cbuf = zio_buf_alloc(lsize);
1379 psize = zio_compress_data(compress, zio->io_data, cbuf, lsize);
1380 if (psize == 0 || psize == lsize) {
1381 compress = ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF;
1382 zio_buf_free(cbuf, lsize);
1383 } else if (!zp->zp_dedup && psize <= BPE_PAYLOAD_SIZE &&
1384 zp->zp_level == 0 && !DMU_OT_HAS_FILL(zp->zp_type) &&
1385 spa_feature_is_enabled(spa, SPA_FEATURE_EMBEDDED_DATA)) {
1386 encode_embedded_bp_compressed(bp,
1387 cbuf, compress, lsize, psize);
1388 BPE_SET_ETYPE(bp, BP_EMBEDDED_TYPE_DATA);
1389 BP_SET_TYPE(bp, zio->io_prop.zp_type);
1390 BP_SET_LEVEL(bp, zio->io_prop.zp_level);
1391 zio_buf_free(cbuf, lsize);
1392 bp->blk_birth = zio->io_txg;
1393 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
1394 ASSERT(spa_feature_is_active(spa,
1395 SPA_FEATURE_EMBEDDED_DATA));
1396 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1397 } else {
1398 /*
1399 * Round up compressed size up to the ashift
1400 * of the smallest-ashift device, and zero the tail.
1401 * This ensures that the compressed size of the BP
1402 * (and thus compressratio property) are correct,
1403 * in that we charge for the padding used to fill out
1404 * the last sector.
1405 */
1406 ASSERT3U(spa->spa_min_ashift, >=, SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT);
1407 size_t rounded = (size_t)P2ROUNDUP(psize,
1408 1ULL << spa->spa_min_ashift);
1409 if (rounded >= lsize) {
1410 compress = ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF;
1411 zio_buf_free(cbuf, lsize);
1412 psize = lsize;
1413 } else {
1414 bzero((char *)cbuf + psize, rounded - psize);
1415 psize = rounded;
1416 zio_push_transform(zio, cbuf,
1417 psize, lsize, NULL);
1418 }
1419 }
1420
1421 /*
1422 * We were unable to handle this as an override bp, treat
1423 * it as a regular write I/O.
1424 */
1425 zio->io_bp_override = NULL;
1426 *bp = zio->io_bp_orig;
1427 zio->io_pipeline = zio->io_orig_pipeline;
1428 }
1429
1430 /*
1431 * The final pass of spa_sync() must be all rewrites, but the first
1432 * few passes offer a trade-off: allocating blocks defers convergence,
1433 * but newly allocated blocks are sequential, so they can be written
1434 * to disk faster. Therefore, we allow the first few passes of
1435 * spa_sync() to allocate new blocks, but force rewrites after that.
1436 * There should only be a handful of blocks after pass 1 in any case.
1437 */
1438 if (!BP_IS_HOLE(bp) && bp->blk_birth == zio->io_txg &&
1439 BP_GET_PSIZE(bp) == psize &&
1440 pass >= zfs_sync_pass_rewrite) {
1441 ASSERT(psize != 0);
1442 enum zio_stage gang_stages = zio->io_pipeline & ZIO_GANG_STAGES;
1443 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_REWRITE_PIPELINE | gang_stages;
1444 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE;
1445 } else {
1446 BP_ZERO(bp);
1447 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_WRITE_PIPELINE;
1448 }
1449
1450 if (psize == 0) {
1451 if (zio->io_bp_orig.blk_birth != 0 &&
1452 spa_feature_is_active(spa, SPA_FEATURE_HOLE_BIRTH)) {
1453 BP_SET_LSIZE(bp, lsize);
1454 BP_SET_TYPE(bp, zp->zp_type);
1455 BP_SET_LEVEL(bp, zp->zp_level);
1456 BP_SET_BIRTH(bp, zio->io_txg, 0);
1457 }
1458 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
1459 } else {
1460 ASSERT(zp->zp_checksum != ZIO_CHECKSUM_GANG_HEADER);
1461 BP_SET_LSIZE(bp, lsize);
1462 BP_SET_TYPE(bp, zp->zp_type);
1463 BP_SET_LEVEL(bp, zp->zp_level);
1464 BP_SET_PSIZE(bp, psize);
1465 BP_SET_COMPRESS(bp, compress);
1466 BP_SET_CHECKSUM(bp, zp->zp_checksum);
1467 BP_SET_DEDUP(bp, zp->zp_dedup);
1468 BP_SET_BYTEORDER(bp, ZFS_HOST_BYTEORDER);
1469 if (zp->zp_dedup) {
1470 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
1471 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE));
1472 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_DDT_WRITE_PIPELINE;
1473 }
1474 if (zp->zp_nopwrite) {
1475 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
1476 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE));
1477 zio->io_pipeline |= ZIO_STAGE_NOP_WRITE;
1478 }
1479 }
1480 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1481}
1482
1483static int
1484zio_free_bp_init(zio_t *zio)
1485{
1486 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
1487
1488 if (zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL) {
1489 if (BP_GET_DEDUP(bp))
1490 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_DDT_FREE_PIPELINE;
1491 }
1492
1493 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1494}
1495
1496/*
1497 * ==========================================================================
1498 * Execute the I/O pipeline
1499 * ==========================================================================
1500 */
1501
1502static void
1503zio_taskq_dispatch(zio_t *zio, zio_taskq_type_t q, boolean_t cutinline)
1504{
1505 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
1506 zio_type_t t = zio->io_type;
1507 int flags = (cutinline ? TQ_FRONT : 0);
1508
1509 ASSERT(q == ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE || q == ZIO_TASKQ_INTERRUPT);
1510
1511 /*
1512 * If we're a config writer or a probe, the normal issue and
1513 * interrupt threads may all be blocked waiting for the config lock.
1514 * In this case, select the otherwise-unused taskq for ZIO_TYPE_NULL.
1515 */
1516 if (zio->io_flags & (ZIO_FLAG_CONFIG_WRITER | ZIO_FLAG_PROBE))
1517 t = ZIO_TYPE_NULL;
1518
1519 /*
1520 * A similar issue exists for the L2ARC write thread until L2ARC 2.0.
1521 */
1522 if (t == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE && zio->io_vd && zio->io_vd->vdev_aux)
1523 t = ZIO_TYPE_NULL;
1524
1525 /*
1526 * If this is a high priority I/O, then use the high priority taskq if
1527 * available.
1528 */
1529 if (zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW &&
1530 spa->spa_zio_taskq[t][q + 1].stqs_count != 0)
1531 q++;
1532
1533 ASSERT3U(q, <, ZIO_TASKQ_TYPES);
1534
1535 /*
1536 * NB: We are assuming that the zio can only be dispatched
1537 * to a single taskq at a time. It would be a grievous error
1538 * to dispatch the zio to another taskq at the same time.
1539 */
1540#if defined(illumos) || !defined(_KERNEL)
1541 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_next == NULL);
1542#elif defined(__NetBSD__)
1543 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_queued == 0);
1544#else
1545 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_task.ta_pending == 0);
1546#endif
1547 spa_taskq_dispatch_ent(spa, t, q, (task_func_t *)zio_execute, zio,
1548 flags, &zio->io_tqent);
1549}
1550
1551static boolean_t
1552zio_taskq_member(zio_t *zio, zio_taskq_type_t q)
1553{
1554 kthread_t *executor = zio->io_executor;
1555 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
1556
1557 for (zio_type_t t = 0; t < ZIO_TYPES; t++) {
1558 spa_taskqs_t *tqs = &spa->spa_zio_taskq[t][q];
1559 uint_t i;
1560 for (i = 0; i < tqs->stqs_count; i++) {
1561 if (taskq_member(tqs->stqs_taskq[i], executor))
1562 return (B_TRUE);
1563 }
1564 }
1565
1566 return (B_FALSE);
1567}
1568
1569static int
1570zio_issue_async(zio_t *zio)
1571{
1572 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, B_FALSE);
1573
1574 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
1575}
1576
1577void
1578zio_interrupt(zio_t *zio)
1579{
1580 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_INTERRUPT, B_FALSE);
1581}
1582
1583void
1584zio_delay_interrupt(zio_t *zio)
1585{
1586 /*
1587 * The timeout_generic() function isn't defined in userspace, so
1588 * rather than trying to implement the function, the zio delay
1589 * functionality has been disabled for userspace builds.
1590 */
1591
1592#ifndef __NetBSD__
1593 /* XXXNETBSD implement timeout_generic() with a callout_t in zio_t */
1594 /*
1595 * If io_target_timestamp is zero, then no delay has been registered
1596 * for this IO, thus jump to the end of this function and "skip" the
1597 * delay; issuing it directly to the zio layer.
1598 */
1599 if (zio->io_target_timestamp != 0) {
1600 hrtime_t now = gethrtime();
1601
1602 if (now >= zio->io_target_timestamp) {
1603 /*
1604 * This IO has already taken longer than the target
1605 * delay to complete, so we don't want to delay it
1606 * any longer; we "miss" the delay and issue it
1607 * directly to the zio layer. This is likely due to
1608 * the target latency being set to a value less than
1609 * the underlying hardware can satisfy (e.g. delay
1610 * set to 1ms, but the disks take 10ms to complete an
1611 * IO request).
1612 */
1613
1614 DTRACE_PROBE2(zio__delay__miss, zio_t *, zio,
1615 hrtime_t, now);
1616
1617 zio_interrupt(zio);
1618 } else {
1619 hrtime_t diff = zio->io_target_timestamp - now;
1620
1621 DTRACE_PROBE3(zio__delay__hit, zio_t *, zio,
1622 hrtime_t, now, hrtime_t, diff);
1623
1624 (void) timeout_generic(CALLOUT_NORMAL,
1625 (void (*)(void *))zio_interrupt, zio, diff, 1, 0);
1626 }
1627
1628 return;
1629 }
1630#endif
1631
1632 DTRACE_PROBE1(zio__delay__skip, zio_t *, zio);
1633 zio_interrupt(zio);
1634}
1635
1636/*
1637 * Execute the I/O pipeline until one of the following occurs:
1638 *
1639 * (1) the I/O completes
1640 * (2) the pipeline stalls waiting for dependent child I/Os
1641 * (3) the I/O issues, so we're waiting for an I/O completion interrupt
1642 * (4) the I/O is delegated by vdev-level caching or aggregation
1643 * (5) the I/O is deferred due to vdev-level queueing
1644 * (6) the I/O is handed off to another thread.
1645 *
1646 * In all cases, the pipeline stops whenever there's no CPU work; it never
1647 * burns a thread in cv_wait().
1648 *
1649 * There's no locking on io_stage because there's no legitimate way
1650 * for multiple threads to be attempting to process the same I/O.
1651 */
1652static zio_pipe_stage_t *zio_pipeline[];
1653
1654void
1655zio_execute(zio_t *zio)
1656{
1657 zio->io_executor = curthread;
1658
1659 ASSERT3U(zio->io_queued_timestamp, >, 0);
1660
1661 while (zio->io_stage < ZIO_STAGE_DONE) {
1662 enum zio_stage pipeline = zio->io_pipeline;
1663 enum zio_stage stage = zio->io_stage;
1664 int rv;
1665
1666 ASSERT(!MUTEX_HELD(&zio->io_lock));
1667 ASSERT(ISP2(stage));
1668 ASSERT(zio->io_stall == NULL);
1669
1670 do {
1671 stage <<= 1;
1672 } while ((stage & pipeline) == 0);
1673
1674 ASSERT(stage <= ZIO_STAGE_DONE);
1675
1676 /*
1677 * If we are in interrupt context and this pipeline stage
1678 * will grab a config lock that is held across I/O,
1679 * or may wait for an I/O that needs an interrupt thread
1680 * to complete, issue async to avoid deadlock.
1681 *
1682 * For VDEV_IO_START, we cut in line so that the io will
1683 * be sent to disk promptly.
1684 */
1685 if ((stage & ZIO_BLOCKING_STAGES) && zio->io_vd == NULL &&
1686 zio_taskq_member(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_INTERRUPT)) {
1687 boolean_t cut = (stage == ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START) ?
1688 zio_requeue_io_start_cut_in_line : B_FALSE;
1689 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, cut);
1690 return;
1691 }
1692
1693 zio->io_stage = stage;
1694 zio->io_pipeline_trace |= zio->io_stage;
1695 rv = zio_pipeline[highbit64(stage) - 1](zio);
1696
1697 if (rv == ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP)
1698 return;
1699
1700 ASSERT(rv == ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
1701 }
1702}
1703
1704/*
1705 * ==========================================================================
1706 * Initiate I/O, either sync or async
1707 * ==========================================================================
1708 */
1709int
1710zio_wait(zio_t *zio)
1711{
1712 int error;
1713
1714 ASSERT(zio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_OPEN);
1715 ASSERT(zio->io_executor == NULL);
1716
1717 zio->io_waiter = curthread;
1718 ASSERT0(zio->io_queued_timestamp);
1719 zio->io_queued_timestamp = gethrtime();
1720
1721 zio_execute(zio);
1722
1723 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
1724 while (zio->io_executor != NULL)
1725 cv_wait(&zio->io_cv, &zio->io_lock);
1726 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
1727
1728 error = zio->io_error;
1729 zio_destroy(zio);
1730
1731 return (error);
1732}
1733
1734void
1735zio_nowait(zio_t *zio)
1736{
1737 ASSERT(zio->io_executor == NULL);
1738
1739 if (zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL &&
1740 zio_unique_parent(zio) == NULL) {
1741 /*
1742 * This is a logical async I/O with no parent to wait for it.
1743 * We add it to the spa_async_root_zio "Godfather" I/O which
1744 * will ensure they complete prior to unloading the pool.
1745 */
1746 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
1747
1748 zio_add_child(spa->spa_async_zio_root[CPU_SEQID], zio);
1749 }
1750
1751 ASSERT0(zio->io_queued_timestamp);
1752 zio->io_queued_timestamp = gethrtime();
1753 zio_execute(zio);
1754}
1755
1756/*
1757 * ==========================================================================
1758 * Reexecute or suspend/resume failed I/O
1759 * ==========================================================================
1760 */
1761
1762static void
1763zio_reexecute(zio_t *pio)
1764{
1765 zio_t *cio, *cio_next;
1766
1767 ASSERT(pio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
1768 ASSERT(pio->io_orig_stage == ZIO_STAGE_OPEN);
1769 ASSERT(pio->io_gang_leader == NULL);
1770 ASSERT(pio->io_gang_tree == NULL);
1771
1772 pio->io_flags = pio->io_orig_flags;
1773 pio->io_stage = pio->io_orig_stage;
1774 pio->io_pipeline = pio->io_orig_pipeline;
1775 pio->io_reexecute = 0;
1776 pio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_REEXECUTED;
1777 pio->io_pipeline_trace = 0;
1778 pio->io_error = 0;
1779 for (int w = 0; w < ZIO_WAIT_TYPES; w++)
1780 pio->io_state[w] = 0;
1781 for (int c = 0; c < ZIO_CHILD_TYPES; c++)
1782 pio->io_child_error[c] = 0;
1783
1784 if (IO_IS_ALLOCATING(pio))
1785 BP_ZERO(pio->io_bp);
1786
1787 /*
1788 * As we reexecute pio's children, new children could be created.
1789 * New children go to the head of pio's io_child_list, however,
1790 * so we will (correctly) not reexecute them. The key is that
1791 * the remainder of pio's io_child_list, from 'cio_next' onward,
1792 * cannot be affected by any side effects of reexecuting 'cio'.
1793 */
1794 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
1795 for (cio = zio_walk_children(pio, &zl); cio != NULL; cio = cio_next) {
1796 cio_next = zio_walk_children(pio, &zl);
1797 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
1798 for (int w = 0; w < ZIO_WAIT_TYPES; w++)
1799 pio->io_children[cio->io_child_type][w]++;
1800 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
1801 zio_reexecute(cio);
1802 }
1803
1804 /*
1805 * Now that all children have been reexecuted, execute the parent.
1806 * We don't reexecute "The Godfather" I/O here as it's the
1807 * responsibility of the caller to wait on him.
1808 */
1809 if (!(pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER)) {
1810 pio->io_queued_timestamp = gethrtime();
1811 zio_execute(pio);
1812 }
1813}
1814
1815void
1816zio_suspend(spa_t *spa, zio_t *zio)
1817{
1818 if (spa_get_failmode(spa) == ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_PANIC)
1819 fm_panic("Pool '%s' has encountered an uncorrectable I/O "
1820 "failure and the failure mode property for this pool "
1821 "is set to panic.", spa_name(spa));
1822
1823 zfs_ereport_post(FM_EREPORT_ZFS_IO_FAILURE, spa, NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
1824
1825 mutex_enter(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1826
1827 if (spa->spa_suspend_zio_root == NULL)
1828 spa->spa_suspend_zio_root = zio_root(spa, NULL, NULL,
1829 ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL | ZIO_FLAG_SPECULATIVE |
1830 ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER);
1831
1832 spa->spa_suspended = B_TRUE;
1833
1834 if (zio != NULL) {
1835 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER));
1836 ASSERT(zio != spa->spa_suspend_zio_root);
1837 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
1838 ASSERT(zio_unique_parent(zio) == NULL);
1839 ASSERT(zio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_DONE);
1840 zio_add_child(spa->spa_suspend_zio_root, zio);
1841 }
1842
1843 mutex_exit(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1844}
1845
1846int
1847zio_resume(spa_t *spa)
1848{
1849 zio_t *pio;
1850
1851 /*
1852 * Reexecute all previously suspended i/o.
1853 */
1854 mutex_enter(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1855 spa->spa_suspended = B_FALSE;
1856 cv_broadcast(&spa->spa_suspend_cv);
1857 pio = spa->spa_suspend_zio_root;
1858 spa->spa_suspend_zio_root = NULL;
1859 mutex_exit(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1860
1861 if (pio == NULL)
1862 return (0);
1863
1864 zio_reexecute(pio);
1865 return (zio_wait(pio));
1866}
1867
1868void
1869zio_resume_wait(spa_t *spa)
1870{
1871 mutex_enter(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1872 while (spa_suspended(spa))
1873 cv_wait(&spa->spa_suspend_cv, &spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1874 mutex_exit(&spa->spa_suspend_lock);
1875}
1876
1877/*
1878 * ==========================================================================
1879 * Gang blocks.
1880 *
1881 * A gang block is a collection of small blocks that looks to the DMU
1882 * like one large block. When zio_dva_allocate() cannot find a block
1883 * of the requested size, due to either severe fragmentation or the pool
1884 * being nearly full, it calls zio_write_gang_block() to construct the
1885 * block from smaller fragments.
1886 *
1887 * A gang block consists of a gang header (zio_gbh_phys_t) and up to
1888 * three (SPA_GBH_NBLKPTRS) gang members. The gang header is just like
1889 * an indirect block: it's an array of block pointers. It consumes
1890 * only one sector and hence is allocatable regardless of fragmentation.
1891 * The gang header's bps point to its gang members, which hold the data.
1892 *
1893 * Gang blocks are self-checksumming, using the bp's <vdev, offset, txg>
1894 * as the verifier to ensure uniqueness of the SHA256 checksum.
1895 * Critically, the gang block bp's blk_cksum is the checksum of the data,
1896 * not the gang header. This ensures that data block signatures (needed for
1897 * deduplication) are independent of how the block is physically stored.
1898 *
1899 * Gang blocks can be nested: a gang member may itself be a gang block.
1900 * Thus every gang block is a tree in which root and all interior nodes are
1901 * gang headers, and the leaves are normal blocks that contain user data.
1902 * The root of the gang tree is called the gang leader.
1903 *
1904 * To perform any operation (read, rewrite, free, claim) on a gang block,
1905 * zio_gang_assemble() first assembles the gang tree (minus data leaves)
1906 * in the io_gang_tree field of the original logical i/o by recursively
1907 * reading the gang leader and all gang headers below it. This yields
1908 * an in-core tree containing the contents of every gang header and the
1909 * bps for every constituent of the gang block.
1910 *
1911 * With the gang tree now assembled, zio_gang_issue() just walks the gang tree
1912 * and invokes a callback on each bp. To free a gang block, zio_gang_issue()
1913 * calls zio_free_gang() -- a trivial wrapper around zio_free() -- for each bp.
1914 * zio_claim_gang() provides a similarly trivial wrapper for zio_claim().
1915 * zio_read_gang() is a wrapper around zio_read() that omits reading gang
1916 * headers, since we already have those in io_gang_tree. zio_rewrite_gang()
1917 * performs a zio_rewrite() of the data or, for gang headers, a zio_rewrite()
1918 * of the gang header plus zio_checksum_compute() of the data to update the
1919 * gang header's blk_cksum as described above.
1920 *
1921 * The two-phase assemble/issue model solves the problem of partial failure --
1922 * what if you'd freed part of a gang block but then couldn't read the
1923 * gang header for another part? Assembling the entire gang tree first
1924 * ensures that all the necessary gang header I/O has succeeded before
1925 * starting the actual work of free, claim, or write. Once the gang tree
1926 * is assembled, free and claim are in-memory operations that cannot fail.
1927 *
1928 * In the event that a gang write fails, zio_dva_unallocate() walks the
1929 * gang tree to immediately free (i.e. insert back into the space map)
1930 * everything we've allocated. This ensures that we don't get ENOSPC
1931 * errors during repeated suspend/resume cycles due to a flaky device.
1932 *
1933 * Gang rewrites only happen during sync-to-convergence. If we can't assemble
1934 * the gang tree, we won't modify the block, so we can safely defer the free
1935 * (knowing that the block is still intact). If we *can* assemble the gang
1936 * tree, then even if some of the rewrites fail, zio_dva_unallocate() will free
1937 * each constituent bp and we can allocate a new block on the next sync pass.
1938 *
1939 * In all cases, the gang tree allows complete recovery from partial failure.
1940 * ==========================================================================
1941 */
1942
1943static zio_t *
1944zio_read_gang(zio_t *pio, blkptr_t *bp, zio_gang_node_t *gn, void *data)
1945{
1946 if (gn != NULL)
1947 return (pio);
1948
1949 return (zio_read(pio, pio->io_spa, bp, data, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp),
1950 NULL, NULL, pio->io_priority, ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio),
1951 &pio->io_bookmark));
1952}
1953
1954zio_t *
1955zio_rewrite_gang(zio_t *pio, blkptr_t *bp, zio_gang_node_t *gn, void *data)
1956{
1957 zio_t *zio;
1958
1959 if (gn != NULL) {
1960 zio = zio_rewrite(pio, pio->io_spa, pio->io_txg, bp,
1961 gn->gn_gbh, SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE, NULL, NULL, pio->io_priority,
1962 ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio), &pio->io_bookmark);
1963 /*
1964 * As we rewrite each gang header, the pipeline will compute
1965 * a new gang block header checksum for it; but no one will
1966 * compute a new data checksum, so we do that here. The one
1967 * exception is the gang leader: the pipeline already computed
1968 * its data checksum because that stage precedes gang assembly.
1969 * (Presently, nothing actually uses interior data checksums;
1970 * this is just good hygiene.)
1971 */
1972 if (gn != pio->io_gang_leader->io_gang_tree) {
1973 zio_checksum_compute(zio, BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp),
1974 data, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp));
1975 }
1976 /*
1977 * If we are here to damage data for testing purposes,
1978 * leave the GBH alone so that we can detect the damage.
1979 */
1980 if (pio->io_gang_leader->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_INDUCE_DAMAGE)
1981 zio->io_pipeline &= ~ZIO_VDEV_IO_STAGES;
1982 } else {
1983 zio = zio_rewrite(pio, pio->io_spa, pio->io_txg, bp,
1984 data, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp), NULL, NULL, pio->io_priority,
1985 ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio), &pio->io_bookmark);
1986 }
1987
1988 return (zio);
1989}
1990
1991/* ARGSUSED */
1992zio_t *
1993zio_free_gang(zio_t *pio, blkptr_t *bp, zio_gang_node_t *gn, void *data)
1994{
1995 return (zio_free_sync(pio, pio->io_spa, pio->io_txg, bp,
1996 BP_IS_GANG(bp) ? SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE : BP_GET_PSIZE(bp),
1997 ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio)));
1998}
1999
2000/* ARGSUSED */
2001zio_t *
2002zio_claim_gang(zio_t *pio, blkptr_t *bp, zio_gang_node_t *gn, void *data)
2003{
2004 return (zio_claim(pio, pio->io_spa, pio->io_txg, bp,
2005 NULL, NULL, ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio)));
2006}

2009 NULL,
2010 zio_read_gang,
2011 zio_rewrite_gang,
2012 zio_free_gang,
2013 zio_claim_gang,
2014 NULL

2060static void
2061zio_gang_tree_assemble(zio_t *gio, blkptr_t *bp, zio_gang_node_t **gnpp)
2062{
2063 zio_gang_node_t *gn = zio_gang_node_alloc(gnpp);
2064
2065 ASSERT(gio->io_gang_leader == gio);
2066 ASSERT(BP_IS_GANG(bp));
2067
2068 zio_nowait(zio_read(gio, gio->io_spa, bp, gn->gn_gbh,
2069 SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE, zio_gang_tree_assemble_done, gn,
2070 gio->io_priority, ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(gio), &gio->io_bookmark));
2071}

2073static void
2074zio_gang_tree_assemble_done(zio_t *zio)
2075{
2076 zio_t *gio = zio->io_gang_leader;
2077 zio_gang_node_t *gn = zio->io_private;
2078 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2079
2080 ASSERT(gio == zio_unique_parent(zio));
2081 ASSERT(zio->io_child_count == 0);
2082
2083 if (zio->io_error)
2084 return;
2085
2086 if (BP_SHOULD_BYTESWAP(bp))
2087 byteswap_uint64_array(zio->io_data, zio->io_size);
2088
2089 ASSERT(zio->io_data == gn->gn_gbh);
2090 ASSERT(zio->io_size == SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE);
2091 ASSERT(gn->gn_gbh->zg_tail.zec_magic == ZEC_MAGIC);
2092
2093 for (int g = 0; g < SPA_GBH_NBLKPTRS; g++) {
2094 blkptr_t *gbp = &gn->gn_gbh->zg_blkptr[g];
2095 if (!BP_IS_GANG(gbp))
2096 continue;
2097 zio_gang_tree_assemble(gio, gbp, &gn->gn_child[g]);
2098 }
2099}
2100
2101static void
2102zio_gang_tree_issue(zio_t *pio, zio_gang_node_t *gn, blkptr_t *bp, void *data)
2103{
2104 zio_t *gio = pio->io_gang_leader;
2105 zio_t *zio;
2106
2107 ASSERT(BP_IS_GANG(bp) == !!gn);
2108 ASSERT(BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) == BP_GET_CHECKSUM(gio->io_bp));
2109 ASSERT(BP_GET_LSIZE(bp) == BP_GET_PSIZE(bp) || gn == gio->io_gang_tree);
2110
2111 /*
2112 * If you're a gang header, your data is in gn->gn_gbh.
2113 * If you're a gang member, your data is in 'data' and gn == NULL.
2114 */
2115 zio = zio_gang_issue_func[gio->io_type](pio, bp, gn, data);
2116
2117 if (gn != NULL) {
2118 ASSERT(gn->gn_gbh->zg_tail.zec_magic == ZEC_MAGIC);
2119
2120 for (int g = 0; g < SPA_GBH_NBLKPTRS; g++) {
2121 blkptr_t *gbp = &gn->gn_gbh->zg_blkptr[g];
2122 if (BP_IS_HOLE(gbp))
2123 continue;
2124 zio_gang_tree_issue(zio, gn->gn_child[g], gbp, data);
2125 data = (char *)data + BP_GET_PSIZE(gbp);
2126 }
2127 }
2128
2129 if (gn == gio->io_gang_tree && gio->io_data != NULL)
2130 ASSERT3P((char *)gio->io_data + gio->io_size, ==, data);
2131
2132 if (zio != pio)
2133 zio_nowait(zio);
2134}

2136static int
2137zio_gang_assemble(zio_t *zio)
2138{
2139 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2140
2141 ASSERT(BP_IS_GANG(bp) && zio->io_gang_leader == NULL);
2142 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type > ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
2143
2144 zio->io_gang_leader = zio;
2145
2146 zio_gang_tree_assemble(zio, bp, &zio->io_gang_tree);
2147
2148 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2149}
2150
2151static int
2152zio_gang_issue(zio_t *zio)
2153{
2154 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2155
2156 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_GANG, ZIO_WAIT_DONE))
2157 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
2158
2159 ASSERT(BP_IS_GANG(bp) && zio->io_gang_leader == zio);
2160 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type > ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
2161
2162 if (zio->io_child_error[ZIO_CHILD_GANG] == 0)
2163 zio_gang_tree_issue(zio, zio->io_gang_tree, bp, zio->io_data);
2164 else
2165 zio_gang_tree_free(&zio->io_gang_tree);
2166
2167 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
2168
2169 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2170}
