2172static void
2173zio_write_gang_member_ready(zio_t *zio)
2174{
2175 zio_t *pio = zio_unique_parent(zio);
2176 zio_t *gio = zio->io_gang_leader;
2177 dva_t *cdva = zio->io_bp->blk_dva;
2178 dva_t *pdva = pio->io_bp->blk_dva;
2179 uint64_t asize;
2180
2181 if (BP_IS_HOLE(zio->io_bp))
2182 return;
2183
2184 ASSERT(BP_IS_HOLE(&zio->io_bp_orig));
2185
2186 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
2187 ASSERT3U(zio->io_prop.zp_copies, ==, gio->io_prop.zp_copies);
2188 ASSERT3U(zio->io_prop.zp_copies, <=, BP_GET_NDVAS(zio->io_bp));
2189 ASSERT3U(pio->io_prop.zp_copies, <=, BP_GET_NDVAS(pio->io_bp));
2190 ASSERT3U(BP_GET_NDVAS(zio->io_bp), <=, BP_GET_NDVAS(pio->io_bp));
2191
2192 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
2193 for (int d = 0; d < BP_GET_NDVAS(zio->io_bp); d++) {
2194 ASSERT(DVA_GET_GANG(&pdva[d]));
2195 asize = DVA_GET_ASIZE(&pdva[d]);
2196 asize += DVA_GET_ASIZE(&cdva[d]);
2197 DVA_SET_ASIZE(&pdva[d], asize);
2198 }
2199 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
2200}
2201
2202static int
2203zio_write_gang_block(zio_t *pio)
2204{
2205 spa_t *spa = pio->io_spa;
2206 metaslab_class_t *mc = spa_normal_class(spa);
2207 blkptr_t *bp = pio->io_bp;
2208 zio_t *gio = pio->io_gang_leader;
2209 zio_t *zio;
2210 zio_gang_node_t *gn, **gnpp;
2211 zio_gbh_phys_t *gbh;
2212 uint64_t txg = pio->io_txg;
2213 uint64_t resid = pio->io_size;
2214 uint64_t lsize;
2215 int copies = gio->io_prop.zp_copies;
2216 int gbh_copies = MIN(copies + 1, spa_max_replication(spa));
2217 zio_prop_t zp;
2218 int error;
2219
2220 int flags = METASLAB_HINTBP_FAVOR | METASLAB_GANG_HEADER;
2221 if (pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING) {
2222 ASSERT(pio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
2223 ASSERT(!(pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA));
2224
2225 flags |= METASLAB_ASYNC_ALLOC;
2226 VERIFY(refcount_held(&mc->mc_alloc_slots, pio));
2227
2228 /*
2229 * The logical zio has already placed a reservation for
2230 * 'copies' allocation slots but gang blocks may require
2231 * additional copies. These additional copies
2232 * (i.e. gbh_copies - copies) are guaranteed to succeed
2233 * since metaslab_class_throttle_reserve() always allows
2234 * additional reservations for gang blocks.
2235 */
2236 VERIFY(metaslab_class_throttle_reserve(mc, gbh_copies - copies,
2237 pio, flags));
2238 }
2239
2240 error = metaslab_alloc(spa, mc, SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE,
2241 bp, gbh_copies, txg, pio == gio ? NULL : gio->io_bp, flags,
2242 &pio->io_alloc_list, pio);
2243 if (error) {
2244 if (pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING) {
2245 ASSERT(pio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
2246 ASSERT(!(pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA));
2247
2248 /*
2249 * If we failed to allocate the gang block header then
2250 * we remove any additional allocation reservations that
2251 * we placed here. The original reservation will
2252 * be removed when the logical I/O goes to the ready
2253 * stage.
2254 */
2255 metaslab_class_throttle_unreserve(mc,
2256 gbh_copies - copies, pio);
2257 }
2258 pio->io_error = error;
2259 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2260 }
2261
2262 if (pio == gio) {
2263 gnpp = &gio->io_gang_tree;
2264 } else {
2265 gnpp = pio->io_private;
2266 ASSERT(pio->io_ready == zio_write_gang_member_ready);
2267 }
2268
2269 gn = zio_gang_node_alloc(gnpp);
2270 gbh = gn->gn_gbh;
2271 bzero(gbh, SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE);
2272
2273 /*
2274 * Create the gang header.
2275 */
2276 zio = zio_rewrite(pio, spa, txg, bp, gbh, SPA_GANGBLOCKSIZE, NULL, NULL,
2277 pio->io_priority, ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio), &pio->io_bookmark);
2278
2279 /*
2280 * Create and nowait the gang children.
2281 */
2282 for (int g = 0; resid != 0; resid -= lsize, g++) {
2283 lsize = P2ROUNDUP(resid / (SPA_GBH_NBLKPTRS - g),
2284 SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE);
2285 ASSERT(lsize >= SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE && lsize <= resid);
2286
2287 zp.zp_checksum = gio->io_prop.zp_checksum;
2288 zp.zp_compress = ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF;
2289 zp.zp_type = DMU_OT_NONE;
2290 zp.zp_level = 0;
2291 zp.zp_copies = gio->io_prop.zp_copies;
2292 zp.zp_dedup = B_FALSE;
2293 zp.zp_dedup_verify = B_FALSE;
2294 zp.zp_nopwrite = B_FALSE;
2295
2296 zio_t *cio = zio_write(zio, spa, txg, &gbh->zg_blkptr[g],
2297 (char *)pio->io_data + (pio->io_size - resid), lsize, &zp,
2298 zio_write_gang_member_ready, NULL, NULL, NULL,
2299 &gn->gn_child[g], pio->io_priority,
2300 ZIO_GANG_CHILD_FLAGS(pio), &pio->io_bookmark);
2301
2302 if (pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING) {
2303 ASSERT(pio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
2304 ASSERT(!(pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA));
2305
2306 /*
2307 * Gang children won't throttle but we should
2308 * account for their work, so reserve an allocation
2309 * slot for them here.
2310 */
2311 VERIFY(metaslab_class_throttle_reserve(mc,
2312 zp.zp_copies, cio, flags));
2313 }
2314 zio_nowait(cio);
2315 }
2316
2317 /*
2318 * Set pio's pipeline to just wait for zio to finish.
2319 */
2320 pio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
2321
2322 zio_nowait(zio);
2323
2324 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2325}
2326
2327/*
2328 * The zio_nop_write stage in the pipeline determines if allocating a
2329 * new bp is necessary. The nopwrite feature can handle writes in
2330 * either syncing or open context (i.e. zil writes) and as a result is
2331 * mutually exclusive with dedup.
2332 *
2333 * By leveraging a cryptographically secure checksum, such as SHA256, we
2334 * can compare the checksums of the new data and the old to determine if
2335 * allocating a new block is required. Note that our requirements for
2336 * cryptographic strength are fairly weak: there can't be any accidental
2337 * hash collisions, but we don't need to be secure against intentional
2338 * (malicious) collisions. To trigger a nopwrite, you have to be able
2339 * to write the file to begin with, and triggering an incorrect (hash
2340 * collision) nopwrite is no worse than simply writing to the file.
2341 * That said, there are no known attacks against the checksum algorithms
2342 * used for nopwrite, assuming that the salt and the checksums
2343 * themselves remain secret.
2344 */
2345static int
2346zio_nop_write(zio_t *zio)
2347{
2348 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2349 blkptr_t *bp_orig = &zio->io_bp_orig;
2350 zio_prop_t *zp = &zio->io_prop;
2351
2352 ASSERT(BP_GET_LEVEL(bp) == 0);
2353 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE));
2354 ASSERT(zp->zp_nopwrite);
2355 ASSERT(!zp->zp_dedup);
2356 ASSERT(zio->io_bp_override == NULL);
2357 ASSERT(IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio));
2358
2359 /*
2360 * Check to see if the original bp and the new bp have matching
2361 * characteristics (i.e. same checksum, compression algorithms, etc).
2362 * If they don't then just continue with the pipeline which will
2363 * allocate a new bp.
2364 */
2365 if (BP_IS_HOLE(bp_orig) ||
2366 !(zio_checksum_table[BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp)].ci_flags &
2367 ZCHECKSUM_FLAG_NOPWRITE) ||
2368 BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) != BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp_orig) ||
2369 BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp) != BP_GET_COMPRESS(bp_orig) ||
2370 BP_GET_DEDUP(bp) != BP_GET_DEDUP(bp_orig) ||
2371 zp->zp_copies != BP_GET_NDVAS(bp_orig))
2372 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2373
2374 /*
2375 * If the checksums match then reset the pipeline so that we
2376 * avoid allocating a new bp and issuing any I/O.
2377 */
2378 if (ZIO_CHECKSUM_EQUAL(bp->blk_cksum, bp_orig->blk_cksum)) {
2379 ASSERT(zio_checksum_table[zp->zp_checksum].ci_flags &
2380 ZCHECKSUM_FLAG_NOPWRITE);
2381 ASSERT3U(BP_GET_PSIZE(bp), ==, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp_orig));
2382 ASSERT3U(BP_GET_LSIZE(bp), ==, BP_GET_LSIZE(bp_orig));
2383 ASSERT(zp->zp_compress != ZIO_COMPRESS_OFF);
2384 ASSERT(bcmp(&bp->blk_prop, &bp_orig->blk_prop,
2385 sizeof (uint64_t)) == 0);
2386
2387 *bp = *bp_orig;
2388 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
2389 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE;
2390 }
2391
2392 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2393}
2394
2395/*
2396 * ==========================================================================
2397 * Dedup
2398 * ==========================================================================
2399 */
2400static void
2401zio_ddt_child_read_done(zio_t *zio)
2402{
2403 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2404 ddt_entry_t *dde = zio->io_private;
2405 ddt_phys_t *ddp;
2406 zio_t *pio = zio_unique_parent(zio);
2407
2408 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
2409 ddp = ddt_phys_select(dde, bp);
2410 if (zio->io_error == 0)
2411 ddt_phys_clear(ddp); /* this ddp doesn't need repair */
2412 if (zio->io_error == 0 && dde->dde_repair_data == NULL)
2413 dde->dde_repair_data = zio->io_data;
2414 else
2415 zio_buf_free(zio->io_data, zio->io_size);
2416 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
2417}
2418
2419static int
2420zio_ddt_read_start(zio_t *zio)
2421{
2422 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2423
2424 ASSERT(BP_GET_DEDUP(bp));
2425 ASSERT(BP_GET_PSIZE(bp) == zio->io_size);
2426 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
2427
2428 if (zio->io_child_error[ZIO_CHILD_DDT]) {
2429 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(zio->io_spa, bp);
2430 ddt_entry_t *dde = ddt_repair_start(ddt, bp);
2431 ddt_phys_t *ddp = dde->dde_phys;
2432 ddt_phys_t *ddp_self = ddt_phys_select(dde, bp);
2433 blkptr_t blk;
2434
2435 ASSERT(zio->io_vsd == NULL);
2436 zio->io_vsd = dde;
2437
2438 if (ddp_self == NULL)
2439 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2440
2441 for (int p = 0; p < DDT_PHYS_TYPES; p++, ddp++) {
2442 if (ddp->ddp_phys_birth == 0 || ddp == ddp_self)
2443 continue;
2444 ddt_bp_create(ddt->ddt_checksum, &dde->dde_key, ddp,
2445 &blk);
2446 zio_nowait(zio_read(zio, zio->io_spa, &blk,
2447 zio_buf_alloc(zio->io_size), zio->io_size,
2448 zio_ddt_child_read_done, dde, zio->io_priority,
2449 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_FLAGS(zio) | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE,
2450 &zio->io_bookmark));
2451 }
2452 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2453 }
2454
2455 zio_nowait(zio_read(zio, zio->io_spa, bp,
2456 zio->io_data, zio->io_size, NULL, NULL, zio->io_priority,
2457 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_FLAGS(zio), &zio->io_bookmark));
2458
2459 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2460}
2461
2462static int
2463zio_ddt_read_done(zio_t *zio)
2464{
2465 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2466
2467 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_DDT, ZIO_WAIT_DONE))
2468 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
2469
2470 ASSERT(BP_GET_DEDUP(bp));
2471 ASSERT(BP_GET_PSIZE(bp) == zio->io_size);
2472 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
2473
2474 if (zio->io_child_error[ZIO_CHILD_DDT]) {
2475 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(zio->io_spa, bp);
2476 ddt_entry_t *dde = zio->io_vsd;
2477 if (ddt == NULL) {
2478 ASSERT(spa_load_state(zio->io_spa) != SPA_LOAD_NONE);
2479 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2480 }
2481 if (dde == NULL) {
2482 zio->io_stage = ZIO_STAGE_DDT_READ_START >> 1;
2483 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, B_FALSE);
2484 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
2485 }
2486 if (dde->dde_repair_data != NULL) {
2487 bcopy(dde->dde_repair_data, zio->io_data, zio->io_size);
2488 zio->io_child_error[ZIO_CHILD_DDT] = 0;
2489 }
2490 ddt_repair_done(ddt, dde);
2491 zio->io_vsd = NULL;
2492 }
2493
2494 ASSERT(zio->io_vsd == NULL);
2495
2496 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2497}
2498
2499static boolean_t
2500zio_ddt_collision(zio_t *zio, ddt_t *ddt, ddt_entry_t *dde)
2501{
2502 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
2503
2504 /*
2505 * Note: we compare the original data, not the transformed data,
2506 * because when zio->io_bp is an override bp, we will not have
2507 * pushed the I/O transforms. That's an important optimization
2508 * because otherwise we'd compress/encrypt all dmu_sync() data twice.
2509 */
2510 for (int p = DDT_PHYS_SINGLE; p <= DDT_PHYS_TRIPLE; p++) {
2511 zio_t *lio = dde->dde_lead_zio[p];
2512
2513 if (lio != NULL) {
2514 return (lio->io_orig_size != zio->io_orig_size ||
2515 bcmp(zio->io_orig_data, lio->io_orig_data,
2516 zio->io_orig_size) != 0);
2517 }
2518 }
2519
2520 for (int p = DDT_PHYS_SINGLE; p <= DDT_PHYS_TRIPLE; p++) {
2521 ddt_phys_t *ddp = &dde->dde_phys[p];
2522
2523 if (ddp->ddp_phys_birth != 0) {
2524 arc_buf_t *abuf = NULL;
2525 arc_flags_t aflags = ARC_FLAG_WAIT;
2526 blkptr_t blk = *zio->io_bp;
2527 int error;
2528
2529 ddt_bp_fill(ddp, &blk, ddp->ddp_phys_birth);
2530
2531 ddt_exit(ddt);
2532
2533 error = arc_read(NULL, spa, &blk,
2534 arc_getbuf_func, &abuf, ZIO_PRIORITY_SYNC_READ,
2535 ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL | ZIO_FLAG_SPECULATIVE,
2536 &aflags, &zio->io_bookmark);
2537
2538 if (error == 0) {
2539 if (arc_buf_size(abuf) != zio->io_orig_size ||
2540 bcmp(abuf->b_data, zio->io_orig_data,
2541 zio->io_orig_size) != 0)
2542 error = SET_ERROR(EEXIST);
2543 arc_buf_destroy(abuf, &abuf);
2544 }
2545
2546 ddt_enter(ddt);
2547 return (error != 0);
2548 }
2549 }
2550
2551 return (B_FALSE);
2552}
2553
2554static void
2555zio_ddt_child_write_ready(zio_t *zio)
2556{
2557 int p = zio->io_prop.zp_copies;
2558 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(zio->io_spa, zio->io_bp);
2559 ddt_entry_t *dde = zio->io_private;
2560 ddt_phys_t *ddp = &dde->dde_phys[p];
2561 zio_t *pio;
2562
2563 if (zio->io_error)
2564 return;
2565
2566 ddt_enter(ddt);
2567
2568 ASSERT(dde->dde_lead_zio[p] == zio);
2569
2570 ddt_phys_fill(ddp, zio->io_bp);
2571
2572 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
2573 while ((pio = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl)) != NULL)
2574 ddt_bp_fill(ddp, pio->io_bp, zio->io_txg);
2575
2576 ddt_exit(ddt);
2577}
2578
2579static void
2580zio_ddt_child_write_done(zio_t *zio)
2581{
2582 int p = zio->io_prop.zp_copies;
2583 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(zio->io_spa, zio->io_bp);
2584 ddt_entry_t *dde = zio->io_private;
2585 ddt_phys_t *ddp = &dde->dde_phys[p];
2586
2587 ddt_enter(ddt);
2588
2589 ASSERT(ddp->ddp_refcnt == 0);
2590 ASSERT(dde->dde_lead_zio[p] == zio);
2591 dde->dde_lead_zio[p] = NULL;
2592
2593 if (zio->io_error == 0) {
2594 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
2595 while (zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl) != NULL)
2596 ddt_phys_addref(ddp);
2597 } else {
2598 ddt_phys_clear(ddp);
2599 }
2600
2601 ddt_exit(ddt);
2602}
2603
2604static void
2605zio_ddt_ditto_write_done(zio_t *zio)
2606{
2607 int p = DDT_PHYS_DITTO;
2608 zio_prop_t *zp = &zio->io_prop;
2609 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2610 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(zio->io_spa, bp);
2611 ddt_entry_t *dde = zio->io_private;
2612 ddt_phys_t *ddp = &dde->dde_phys[p];
2613 ddt_key_t *ddk = &dde->dde_key;
2614
2615 ddt_enter(ddt);
2616
2617 ASSERT(ddp->ddp_refcnt == 0);
2618 ASSERT(dde->dde_lead_zio[p] == zio);
2619 dde->dde_lead_zio[p] = NULL;
2620
2621 if (zio->io_error == 0) {
2622 ASSERT(ZIO_CHECKSUM_EQUAL(bp->blk_cksum, ddk->ddk_cksum));
2623 ASSERT(zp->zp_copies < SPA_DVAS_PER_BP);
2624 ASSERT(zp->zp_copies == BP_GET_NDVAS(bp) - BP_IS_GANG(bp));
2625 if (ddp->ddp_phys_birth != 0)
2626 ddt_phys_free(ddt, ddk, ddp, zio->io_txg);
2627 ddt_phys_fill(ddp, bp);
2628 }
2629
2630 ddt_exit(ddt);
2631}
2632
2633static int
2634zio_ddt_write(zio_t *zio)
2635{
2636 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
2637 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2638 uint64_t txg = zio->io_txg;
2639 zio_prop_t *zp = &zio->io_prop;
2640 int p = zp->zp_copies;
2641 int ditto_copies;
2642 zio_t *cio = NULL;
2643 zio_t *dio = NULL;
2644 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(spa, bp);
2645 ddt_entry_t *dde;
2646 ddt_phys_t *ddp;
2647
2648 ASSERT(BP_GET_DEDUP(bp));
2649 ASSERT(BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp) == zp->zp_checksum);
2650 ASSERT(BP_IS_HOLE(bp) || zio->io_bp_override);
2651
2652 ddt_enter(ddt);
2653 dde = ddt_lookup(ddt, bp, B_TRUE);
2654 ddp = &dde->dde_phys[p];
2655
2656 if (zp->zp_dedup_verify && zio_ddt_collision(zio, ddt, dde)) {
2657 /*
2658 * If we're using a weak checksum, upgrade to a strong checksum
2659 * and try again. If we're already using a strong checksum,
2660 * we can't resolve it, so just convert to an ordinary write.
2661 * (And automatically e-mail a paper to Nature?)
2662 */
2663 if (!(zio_checksum_table[zp->zp_checksum].ci_flags &
2664 ZCHECKSUM_FLAG_DEDUP)) {
2665 zp->zp_checksum = spa_dedup_checksum(spa);
2666 zio_pop_transforms(zio);
2667 zio->io_stage = ZIO_STAGE_OPEN;
2668 BP_ZERO(bp);
2669 } else {
2670 zp->zp_dedup = B_FALSE;
2671 }
2672 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_WRITE_PIPELINE;
2673 ddt_exit(ddt);
2674 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2675 }
2676
2677 ditto_copies = ddt_ditto_copies_needed(ddt, dde, ddp);
2678 ASSERT(ditto_copies < SPA_DVAS_PER_BP);
2679
2680 if (ditto_copies > ddt_ditto_copies_present(dde) &&
2681 dde->dde_lead_zio[DDT_PHYS_DITTO] == NULL) {
2682 zio_prop_t czp = *zp;
2683
2684 czp.zp_copies = ditto_copies;
2685
2686 /*
2687 * If we arrived here with an override bp, we won't have run
2688 * the transform stack, so we won't have the data we need to
2689 * generate a child i/o. So, toss the override bp and restart.
2690 * This is safe, because using the override bp is just an
2691 * optimization; and it's rare, so the cost doesn't matter.
2692 */
2693 if (zio->io_bp_override) {
2694 zio_pop_transforms(zio);
2695 zio->io_stage = ZIO_STAGE_OPEN;
2696 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_WRITE_PIPELINE;
2697 zio->io_bp_override = NULL;
2698 BP_ZERO(bp);
2699 ddt_exit(ddt);
2700 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2701 }
2702
2703 dio = zio_write(zio, spa, txg, bp, zio->io_orig_data,
2704 zio->io_orig_size, &czp, NULL, NULL,
2705 NULL, zio_ddt_ditto_write_done, dde, zio->io_priority,
2706 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_FLAGS(zio), &zio->io_bookmark);
2707
2708 zio_push_transform(dio, zio->io_data, zio->io_size, 0, NULL);
2709 dde->dde_lead_zio[DDT_PHYS_DITTO] = dio;
2710 }
2711
2712 if (ddp->ddp_phys_birth != 0 || dde->dde_lead_zio[p] != NULL) {
2713 if (ddp->ddp_phys_birth != 0)
2714 ddt_bp_fill(ddp, bp, txg);
2715 if (dde->dde_lead_zio[p] != NULL)
2716 zio_add_child(zio, dde->dde_lead_zio[p]);
2717 else
2718 ddt_phys_addref(ddp);
2719 } else if (zio->io_bp_override) {
2720 ASSERT(bp->blk_birth == txg);
2721 ASSERT(BP_EQUAL(bp, zio->io_bp_override));
2722 ddt_phys_fill(ddp, bp);
2723 ddt_phys_addref(ddp);
2724 } else {
2725 cio = zio_write(zio, spa, txg, bp, zio->io_orig_data,
2726 zio->io_orig_size, zp,
2727 zio_ddt_child_write_ready, NULL, NULL,
2728 zio_ddt_child_write_done, dde, zio->io_priority,
2729 ZIO_DDT_CHILD_FLAGS(zio), &zio->io_bookmark);
2730
2731 zio_push_transform(cio, zio->io_data, zio->io_size, 0, NULL);
2732 dde->dde_lead_zio[p] = cio;
2733 }
2734
2735 ddt_exit(ddt);
2736
2737 if (cio)
2738 zio_nowait(cio);
2739 if (dio)
2740 zio_nowait(dio);
2741
2742 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2743}
2744
2745ddt_entry_t *freedde; /* for debugging */
2746
2747static int
2748zio_ddt_free(zio_t *zio)
2749{
2750 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
2751 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2752 ddt_t *ddt = ddt_select(spa, bp);
2753 ddt_entry_t *dde;
2754 ddt_phys_t *ddp;
2755
2756 ASSERT(BP_GET_DEDUP(bp));
2757 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
2758
2759 ddt_enter(ddt);
2760 freedde = dde = ddt_lookup(ddt, bp, B_TRUE);
2761 ddp = ddt_phys_select(dde, bp);
2762 ddt_phys_decref(ddp);
2763 ddt_exit(ddt);
2764
2765 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2766}
2767
2768/*
2769 * ==========================================================================
2770 * Allocate and free blocks
2771 * ==========================================================================
2772 */
2773
2774static zio_t *
2775zio_io_to_allocate(spa_t *spa)
2776{
2777 zio_t *zio;
2778
2779 ASSERT(MUTEX_HELD(&spa->spa_alloc_lock));
2780
2781 zio = avl_first(&spa->spa_alloc_tree);
2782 if (zio == NULL)
2783 return (NULL);
2784
2785 ASSERT(IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio));
2786
2787 /*
2788 * Try to place a reservation for this zio. If we're unable to
2789 * reserve then we throttle.
2790 */
2791 if (!metaslab_class_throttle_reserve(spa_normal_class(spa),
2792 zio->io_prop.zp_copies, zio, 0)) {
2793 return (NULL);
2794 }
2795
2796 avl_remove(&spa->spa_alloc_tree, zio);
2797 ASSERT3U(zio->io_stage, <, ZIO_STAGE_DVA_ALLOCATE);
2798
2799 return (zio);
2800}
2801
2802static int
2803zio_dva_throttle(zio_t *zio)
2804{
2805 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
2806 zio_t *nio;
2807
2808 if (zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_SYNC_WRITE ||
2809 !spa_normal_class(zio->io_spa)->mc_alloc_throttle_enabled ||
2810 zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG ||
2811 zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA) {
2812 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2813 }
2814
2815 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type > ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
2816
2817 ASSERT3U(zio->io_queued_timestamp, >, 0);
2818 ASSERT(zio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_DVA_THROTTLE);
2819
2820 mutex_enter(&spa->spa_alloc_lock);
2821
2822 ASSERT(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
2823 avl_add(&spa->spa_alloc_tree, zio);
2824
2825 nio = zio_io_to_allocate(zio->io_spa);
2826 mutex_exit(&spa->spa_alloc_lock);
2827
2828 if (nio == zio)
2829 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2830
2831 if (nio != NULL) {
2832 ASSERT3U(nio->io_queued_timestamp, <=,
2833 zio->io_queued_timestamp);
2834 ASSERT(nio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_DVA_THROTTLE);
2835 /*
2836 * We are passing control to a new zio so make sure that
2837 * it is processed by a different thread. We do this to
2838 * avoid stack overflows that can occur when parents are
2839 * throttled and children are making progress. We allow
2840 * it to go to the head of the taskq since it's already
2841 * been waiting.
2842 */
2843 zio_taskq_dispatch(nio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, B_TRUE);
2844 }
2845 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
2846}
2847
2848void
2849zio_allocate_dispatch(spa_t *spa)
2850{
2851 zio_t *zio;
2852
2853 mutex_enter(&spa->spa_alloc_lock);
2854 zio = zio_io_to_allocate(spa);
2855 mutex_exit(&spa->spa_alloc_lock);
2856 if (zio == NULL)
2857 return;
2858
2859 ASSERT3U(zio->io_stage, ==, ZIO_STAGE_DVA_THROTTLE);
2860 ASSERT0(zio->io_error);
2861 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, B_TRUE);
2862}

2864static int
2865zio_dva_allocate(zio_t *zio)
2866{
2867 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
2868 metaslab_class_t *mc = spa_normal_class(spa);
2869 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
2870 int error;
2871 int flags = 0;
2872
2873 if (zio->io_gang_leader == NULL) {
2874 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type > ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
2875 zio->io_gang_leader = zio;
2876 }
2877
2878 ASSERT(BP_IS_HOLE(bp));
2879 ASSERT0(BP_GET_NDVAS(bp));
2880 ASSERT3U(zio->io_prop.zp_copies, >, 0);
2881 ASSERT3U(zio->io_prop.zp_copies, <=, spa_max_replication(spa));
2882 ASSERT3U(zio->io_size, ==, BP_GET_PSIZE(bp));
2883
2884 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA) {
2885 flags |= METASLAB_DONT_THROTTLE;
2886 }
2887 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GANG_CHILD) {
2888 flags |= METASLAB_GANG_CHILD;
2889 }
2890 if (zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE) {
2891 flags |= METASLAB_ASYNC_ALLOC;
2892 }
2893
2894 error = metaslab_alloc(spa, mc, zio->io_size, bp,
2895 zio->io_prop.zp_copies, zio->io_txg, NULL, flags,
2896 &zio->io_alloc_list, zio);
2897
2898 if (error != 0) {
2899 spa_dbgmsg(spa, "%s: metaslab allocation failure: zio %p, "
2900 "size %llu, error %d", spa_name(spa), zio, zio->io_size,
2901 error);
2902 if (error == ENOSPC && zio->io_size > SPA_MINBLOCKSIZE)
2903 return (zio_write_gang_block(zio));
2904 zio->io_error = error;
2905 }
2906
2907 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
2908}

3013/*
3014 * Issue an I/O to the underlying vdev. Typically the issue pipeline
3015 * stops after this stage and will resume upon I/O completion.
3016 * However, there are instances where the vdev layer may need to
3017 * continue the pipeline when an I/O was not issued. Since the I/O
3018 * that was sent to the vdev layer might be different than the one
3019 * currently active in the pipeline (see vdev_queue_io()), we explicitly
3020 * force the underlying vdev layers to call either zio_execute() or
3021 * zio_interrupt() to ensure that the pipeline continues with the correct I/O.
3022 */
3023static int
3024zio_vdev_io_start(zio_t *zio)
3025{
3026 vdev_t *vd = zio->io_vd;
3027 uint64_t align;
3028 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
3029 int ret;
3030
3031 ASSERT(zio->io_error == 0);
3032 ASSERT(zio->io_child_error[ZIO_CHILD_VDEV] == 0);
3033
3034 if (vd == NULL) {
3035 if (!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_CONFIG_WRITER))
3036 spa_config_enter(spa, SCL_ZIO, zio, RW_READER);
3037
3038 /*
3039 * The mirror_ops handle multiple DVAs in a single BP.
3040 */
3041 vdev_mirror_ops.vdev_op_io_start(zio);
3042 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3043 }
3044
3045 if (vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf && zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE &&
3046 zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW) {
3047 trim_map_free(vd, zio->io_offset, zio->io_size, zio->io_txg);
3048 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3049 }
3050
3051 ASSERT3P(zio->io_logical, !=, zio);
3052
3053 /*
3054 * We keep track of time-sensitive I/Os so that the scan thread
3055 * can quickly react to certain workloads. In particular, we care
3056 * about non-scrubbing, top-level reads and writes with the following
3057 * characteristics:
3058 * - synchronous writes of user data to non-slog devices
3059 * - any reads of user data
3060 * When these conditions are met, adjust the timestamp of spa_last_io
3061 * which allows the scan thread to adjust its workload accordingly.
3062 */
3063 if (!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_SCAN_THREAD) && zio->io_bp != NULL &&
3064 vd == vd->vdev_top && !vd->vdev_islog &&
3065 zio->io_bookmark.zb_objset != DMU_META_OBJSET &&
3066 zio->io_txg != spa_syncing_txg(spa)) {
3067 uint64_t old = spa->spa_last_io;
3068 uint64_t new = ddi_get_lbolt64();
3069 if (old != new)
3070 (void) atomic_cas_64(&spa->spa_last_io, old, new);
3071 }
3072
3073 align = 1ULL << vd->vdev_top->vdev_ashift;
3074
3075 if (!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_PHYSICAL) &&
3076 P2PHASE(zio->io_size, align) != 0) {
3077 /* Transform logical writes to be a full physical block size. */
3078 uint64_t asize = P2ROUNDUP(zio->io_size, align);
3079 char *abuf = NULL;
3080 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ ||
3081 zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE)
3082 abuf = zio_buf_alloc(asize);
3083 ASSERT(vd == vd->vdev_top);
3084 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE) {
3085 bcopy(zio->io_data, abuf, zio->io_size);
3086 bzero(abuf + zio->io_size, asize - zio->io_size);
3087 }
3088 zio_push_transform(zio, abuf, asize, abuf ? asize : 0,
3089 zio_subblock);
3090 }
3091
3092 /*
3093 * If this is not a physical io, make sure that it is properly aligned
3094 * before proceeding.
3095 */
3096 if (!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_PHYSICAL)) {
3097 ASSERT0(P2PHASE(zio->io_offset, align));
3098 ASSERT0(P2PHASE(zio->io_size, align));
3099 } else {
3100 /*
3101 * For the physical io we allow alignment
3102 * to a logical block size.
3103 */
3104 uint64_t log_align =
3105 1ULL << vd->vdev_top->vdev_logical_ashift;
3106 ASSERT0(P2PHASE(zio->io_offset, log_align));
3107 ASSERT0(P2PHASE(zio->io_size, log_align));
3108 }
3109
3110 VERIFY(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ || spa_writeable(spa));
3111
3112 /*
3113 * If this is a repair I/O, and there's no self-healing involved --
3114 * that is, we're just resilvering what we expect to resilver --
3115 * then don't do the I/O unless zio's txg is actually in vd's DTL.
3116 * This prevents spurious resilvering with nested replication.
3117 * For example, given a mirror of mirrors, (A+B)+(C+D), if only
3118 * A is out of date, we'll read from C+D, then use the data to
3119 * resilver A+B -- but we don't actually want to resilver B, just A.
3120 * The top-level mirror has no way to know this, so instead we just
3121 * discard unnecessary repairs as we work our way down the vdev tree.
3122 * The same logic applies to any form of nested replication:
3123 * ditto + mirror, RAID-Z + replacing, etc. This covers them all.
3124 */
3125 if ((zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR) &&
3126 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_SELF_HEAL) &&
3127 zio->io_txg != 0 && /* not a delegated i/o */
3128 !vdev_dtl_contains(vd, DTL_PARTIAL, zio->io_txg, 1)) {
3129 ASSERT(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
3130 zio_vdev_io_bypass(zio);
3131 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3132 }
3133
3134 if (vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf) {
3135 switch (zio->io_type) {
3136 case ZIO_TYPE_READ:
3137 if (vdev_cache_read(zio))
3138 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3139 /* FALLTHROUGH */
3140 case ZIO_TYPE_WRITE:
3141 case ZIO_TYPE_FREE:
3142 if ((zio = vdev_queue_io(zio)) == NULL)
3143 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3144
3145 if (!vdev_accessible(vd, zio)) {
3146 zio->io_error = SET_ERROR(ENXIO);
3147 zio_interrupt(zio);
3148 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3149 }
3150 break;
3151 }
3152 /*
3153 * Note that we ignore repair writes for TRIM because they can
3154 * conflict with normal writes. This isn't an issue because, by
3155 * definition, we only repair blocks that aren't freed.
3156 */
3157 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE &&
3158 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR) &&
3159 !trim_map_write_start(zio))
3160 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3161 }
3162
3163 vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_io_start(zio);
3164 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3165}
3166
3167static int
3168zio_vdev_io_done(zio_t *zio)
3169{
3170 vdev_t *vd = zio->io_vd;
3171 vdev_ops_t *ops = vd ? vd->vdev_ops : &vdev_mirror_ops;
3172 boolean_t unexpected_error = B_FALSE;
3173
3174 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV, ZIO_WAIT_DONE))
3175 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3176
3177 ASSERT(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ ||
3178 zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE || zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE);
3179
3180 if (vd != NULL && vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf &&
3181 (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ || zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE ||
3182 zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE)) {
3183
3184 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE &&
3185 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR))
3186 trim_map_write_done(zio);
3187
3188 vdev_queue_io_done(zio);
3189
3190 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE)
3191 vdev_cache_write(zio);
3192
3193 if (zio_injection_enabled && zio->io_error == 0)
3194 zio->io_error = zio_handle_device_injection(vd,
3195 zio, EIO);
3196
3197 if (zio_injection_enabled && zio->io_error == 0)
3198 zio->io_error = zio_handle_label_injection(zio, EIO);
3199
3200 if (zio->io_error) {
3201 if (zio->io_error == ENOTSUP &&
3202 zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE) {
3203 /* Not all devices support TRIM. */
3204 } else if (!vdev_accessible(vd, zio)) {
3205 zio->io_error = SET_ERROR(ENXIO);
3206 } else {
3207 unexpected_error = B_TRUE;
3208 }
3209 }
3210 }
3211
3212 ops->vdev_op_io_done(zio);
3213
3214 if (unexpected_error)
3215 VERIFY(vdev_probe(vd, zio) == NULL);
3216
3217 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3218}

3246static int
3247zio_vdev_io_assess(zio_t *zio)
3248{
3249 vdev_t *vd = zio->io_vd;
3250
3251 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV, ZIO_WAIT_DONE))
3252 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3253
3254 if (vd == NULL && !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_CONFIG_WRITER))
3255 spa_config_exit(zio->io_spa, SCL_ZIO, zio);
3256
3257 if (zio->io_vsd != NULL) {
3258 zio->io_vsd_ops->vsd_free(zio);
3259 zio->io_vsd = NULL;
3260 }
3261
3262 if (zio_injection_enabled && zio->io_error == 0)
3263 zio->io_error = zio_handle_fault_injection(zio, EIO);
3264
3265 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE &&
3266 zio->io_priority != ZIO_PRIORITY_NOW) {
3267 switch (zio->io_error) {
3268 case 0:
3269 ZIO_TRIM_STAT_INCR(bytes, zio->io_size);
3270 ZIO_TRIM_STAT_BUMP(success);
3271 break;
3272 case EOPNOTSUPP:
3273 ZIO_TRIM_STAT_BUMP(unsupported);
3274 break;
3275 default:
3276 ZIO_TRIM_STAT_BUMP(failed);
3277 break;
3278 }
3279 }
3280
3281 /*
3282 * If the I/O failed, determine whether we should attempt to retry it.
3283 *
3284 * On retry, we cut in line in the issue queue, since we don't want
3285 * compression/checksumming/etc. work to prevent our (cheap) IO reissue.
3286 */
3287 if (zio->io_error && vd == NULL &&
3288 !(zio->io_flags & (ZIO_FLAG_DONT_RETRY | ZIO_FLAG_IO_RETRY))) {
3289 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_DONT_QUEUE)); /* not a leaf */
3290 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_BYPASS)); /* not a leaf */
3291 zio->io_error = 0;
3292 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_IO_RETRY |
3293 ZIO_FLAG_DONT_CACHE | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_AGGREGATE;
3294 zio->io_stage = ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START >> 1;
3295 zio_taskq_dispatch(zio, ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE,
3296 zio_requeue_io_start_cut_in_line);
3297 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3298 }
3299
3300 /*
3301 * If we got an error on a leaf device, convert it to ENXIO
3302 * if the device is not accessible at all.
3303 */
3304 if (zio->io_error && vd != NULL && vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf &&
3305 !vdev_accessible(vd, zio))
3306 zio->io_error = SET_ERROR(ENXIO);
3307
3308 /*
3309 * If we can't write to an interior vdev (mirror or RAID-Z),
3310 * set vdev_cant_write so that we stop trying to allocate from it.
3311 */
3312 if (zio->io_error == ENXIO && zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE &&
3313 vd != NULL && !vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf) {
3314 vd->vdev_cant_write = B_TRUE;
3315 }
3316
3317 if (zio->io_error)
3318 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
3319
3320 if (vd != NULL && vd->vdev_ops->vdev_op_leaf &&
3321 zio->io_physdone != NULL) {
3322 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_DELEGATED));
3323 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_VDEV);
3324 zio->io_physdone(zio->io_logical);
3325 }
3326
3327 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3328}

3333 ASSERT(zio->io_stage == ZIO_STAGE_VDEV_IO_START);

3357/*
3358 * ==========================================================================
3359 * Generate and verify checksums
3360 * ==========================================================================
3361 */
3362static int
3363zio_checksum_generate(zio_t *zio)
3364{
3365 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
3366 enum zio_checksum checksum;
3367
3368 if (bp == NULL) {
3369 /*
3370 * This is zio_write_phys().
3371 * We're either generating a label checksum, or none at all.
3372 */
3373 checksum = zio->io_prop.zp_checksum;
3374
3375 if (checksum == ZIO_CHECKSUM_OFF)
3376 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3377
3378 ASSERT(checksum == ZIO_CHECKSUM_LABEL);
3379 } else {
3380 if (BP_IS_GANG(bp) && zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG) {
3381 ASSERT(!IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio));
3382 checksum = ZIO_CHECKSUM_GANG_HEADER;
3383 } else {
3384 checksum = BP_GET_CHECKSUM(bp);
3385 }
3386 }
3387
3388 zio_checksum_compute(zio, checksum, zio->io_data, zio->io_size);
3389
3390 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3391}
3392
3393static int
3394zio_checksum_verify(zio_t *zio)
3395{
3396 zio_bad_cksum_t info;
3397 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
3398 int error;
3399
3400 ASSERT(zio->io_vd != NULL);
3401
3402 if (bp == NULL) {
3403 /*
3404 * This is zio_read_phys().
3405 * We're either verifying a label checksum, or nothing at all.
3406 */
3407 if (zio->io_prop.zp_checksum == ZIO_CHECKSUM_OFF)
3408 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3409
3410 ASSERT(zio->io_prop.zp_checksum == ZIO_CHECKSUM_LABEL);
3411 }
3412
3413 if ((error = zio_checksum_error(zio, &info)) != 0) {
3414 zio->io_error = error;
3415 if (error == ECKSUM &&
3416 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_SPECULATIVE)) {
3417 zfs_ereport_start_checksum(zio->io_spa,
3418 zio->io_vd, zio, zio->io_offset,
3419 zio->io_size, NULL, &info);
3420 }
3421 }
3422
3423 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3424}

3427 * Called by RAID-Z to ensure we don't compute the checksum twice.
3428 */
3429void

3431{
3432 zio->io_pipeline &= ~ZIO_STAGE_CHECKSUM_VERIFY;

3434
3435/*
3436 * ==========================================================================
3437 * Error rank. Error are ranked in the order 0, ENXIO, ECKSUM, EIO, other.
3438 * An error of 0 indicates success. ENXIO indicates whole-device failure,
3439 * which may be transient (e.g. unplugged) or permament. ECKSUM and EIO
3440 * indicate errors that are specific to one I/O, and most likely permanent.
3441 * Any other error is presumed to be worse because we weren't expecting it.
3442 * ==========================================================================
3443 */
3444int
3445zio_worst_error(int e1, int e2)
3446{
3447 static int zio_error_rank[] = { 0, ENXIO, ECKSUM, EIO };
3448 int r1, r2;
3449
3450 for (r1 = 0; r1 < sizeof (zio_error_rank) / sizeof (int); r1++)
3451 if (e1 == zio_error_rank[r1])
3452 break;
3453
3454 for (r2 = 0; r2 < sizeof (zio_error_rank) / sizeof (int); r2++)
3455 if (e2 == zio_error_rank[r2])
3456 break;
3457
3458 return (r1 > r2 ? e1 : e2);
3459}
3460
3461/*
3462 * ==========================================================================
3463 * I/O completion
3464 * ==========================================================================
3465 */
3466static int
3467zio_ready(zio_t *zio)
3468{
3469 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
3470 zio_t *pio, *pio_next;
3471 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
3472
3473 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_GANG, ZIO_WAIT_READY) ||
3474 zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_DDT, ZIO_WAIT_READY))
3475 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3476
3477 if (zio->io_ready) {
3478 ASSERT(IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio));
3479 ASSERT(bp->blk_birth == zio->io_txg || BP_IS_HOLE(bp) ||
3480 (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE));
3481 ASSERT(zio->io_children[ZIO_CHILD_GANG][ZIO_WAIT_READY] == 0);
3482
3483 zio->io_ready(zio);
3484 }
3485
3486 if (bp != NULL && bp != &zio->io_bp_copy)
3487 zio->io_bp_copy = *bp;
3488
3489 if (zio->io_error != 0) {
3490 zio->io_pipeline = ZIO_INTERLOCK_PIPELINE;
3491
3492 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING) {
3493 ASSERT(IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio));
3494 ASSERT(zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
3495 /*
3496 * We were unable to allocate anything, unreserve and
3497 * issue the next I/O to allocate.
3498 */
3499 metaslab_class_throttle_unreserve(
3500 spa_normal_class(zio->io_spa),
3501 zio->io_prop.zp_copies, zio);
3502 zio_allocate_dispatch(zio->io_spa);
3503 }
3504 }
3505
3506 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
3507 zio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_READY] = 1;
3508 pio = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl);
3509 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
3510
3511 /*
3512 * As we notify zio's parents, new parents could be added.
3513 * New parents go to the head of zio's io_parent_list, however,
3514 * so we will (correctly) not notify them. The remainder of zio's
3515 * io_parent_list, from 'pio_next' onward, cannot change because
3516 * all parents must wait for us to be done before they can be done.
3517 */
3518 for (; pio != NULL; pio = pio_next) {
3519 pio_next = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl);
3520 zio_notify_parent(pio, zio, ZIO_WAIT_READY);
3521 }
3522
3523 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA) {
3524 if (BP_IS_GANG(bp)) {
3525 zio->io_flags &= ~ZIO_FLAG_NODATA;
3526 } else {
3527 ASSERT((uintptr_t)zio->io_data < SPA_MAXBLOCKSIZE);
3528 zio->io_pipeline &= ~ZIO_VDEV_IO_STAGES;
3529 }
3530 }
3531
3532 if (zio_injection_enabled &&
3533 zio->io_spa->spa_syncing_txg == zio->io_txg)
3534 zio_handle_ignored_writes(zio);
3535
3536 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_CONTINUE);
3537}

3539/*
3540 * Update the allocation throttle accounting.
3541 */
3542static void
3543zio_dva_throttle_done(zio_t *zio)
3544{
3545 zio_t *lio = zio->io_logical;
3546 zio_t *pio = zio_unique_parent(zio);
3547 vdev_t *vd = zio->io_vd;
3548 int flags = METASLAB_ASYNC_ALLOC;
3549
3550 ASSERT3P(zio->io_bp, !=, NULL);
3551 ASSERT3U(zio->io_type, ==, ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
3552 ASSERT3U(zio->io_priority, ==, ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
3553 ASSERT3U(zio->io_child_type, ==, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV);
3554 ASSERT(vd != NULL);
3555 ASSERT3P(vd, ==, vd->vdev_top);
3556 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & (ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR | ZIO_FLAG_IO_RETRY)));
3557 ASSERT(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING);
3558 ASSERT(!(lio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE));
3559 ASSERT(!(lio->io_orig_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NODATA));
3560
3561 /*
3562 * Parents of gang children can have two flavors -- ones that
3563 * allocated the gang header (will have ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE set)
3564 * and ones that allocated the constituent blocks. The allocation
3565 * throttle needs to know the allocating parent zio so we must find
3566 * it here.
3567 */
3568 if (pio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_GANG) {
3569 /*
3570 * If our parent is a rewrite gang child then our grandparent
3571 * would have been the one that performed the allocation.
3572 */
3573 if (pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE)
3574 pio = zio_unique_parent(pio);
3575 flags |= METASLAB_GANG_CHILD;
3576 }
3577
3578 ASSERT(IO_IS_ALLOCATING(pio));
3579 ASSERT3P(zio, !=, zio->io_logical);
3580 ASSERT(zio->io_logical != NULL);
3581 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR));
3582 ASSERT0(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE);
3583
3584 mutex_enter(&pio->io_lock);
3585 metaslab_group_alloc_decrement(zio->io_spa, vd->vdev_id, pio, flags);
3586 mutex_exit(&pio->io_lock);
3587
3588 metaslab_class_throttle_unreserve(spa_normal_class(zio->io_spa),
3589 1, pio);
3590
3591 /*
3592 * Call into the pipeline to see if there is more work that
3593 * needs to be done. If there is work to be done it will be
3594 * dispatched to another taskq thread.
3595 */
3596 zio_allocate_dispatch(zio->io_spa);
3597}
3598
3599static int
3600zio_done(zio_t *zio)
3601{
3602 spa_t *spa = zio->io_spa;
3603 zio_t *lio = zio->io_logical;
3604 blkptr_t *bp = zio->io_bp;
3605 vdev_t *vd = zio->io_vd;
3606 uint64_t psize = zio->io_size;
3607 zio_t *pio, *pio_next;
3608 metaslab_class_t *mc = spa_normal_class(spa);
3609 zio_link_t *zl = NULL;
3610
3611 /*
3612 * If our children haven't all completed,
3613 * wait for them and then repeat this pipeline stage.
3614 */
3615 if (zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV, ZIO_WAIT_DONE) ||
3616 zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_GANG, ZIO_WAIT_DONE) ||
3617 zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_DDT, ZIO_WAIT_DONE) ||
3618 zio_wait_for_children(zio, ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL, ZIO_WAIT_DONE))
3619 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3620
3621 /*
3622 * If the allocation throttle is enabled, then update the accounting.
3623 * We only track child I/Os that are part of an allocating async
3624 * write. We must do this since the allocation is performed
3625 * by the logical I/O but the actual write is done by child I/Os.
3626 */
3627 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING &&
3628 zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_VDEV) {
3629 ASSERT(mc->mc_alloc_throttle_enabled);
3630 zio_dva_throttle_done(zio);
3631 }
3632
3633 /*
3634 * If the allocation throttle is enabled, verify that
3635 * we have decremented the refcounts for every I/O that was throttled.
3636 */
3637 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_ALLOCATING) {
3638 ASSERT(zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE);
3639 ASSERT(zio->io_priority == ZIO_PRIORITY_ASYNC_WRITE);
3640 ASSERT(bp != NULL);
3641 metaslab_group_alloc_verify(spa, zio->io_bp, zio);
3642 VERIFY(refcount_not_held(&mc->mc_alloc_slots, zio));
3643 }
3644
3645 for (int c = 0; c < ZIO_CHILD_TYPES; c++)
3646 for (int w = 0; w < ZIO_WAIT_TYPES; w++)
3647 ASSERT(zio->io_children[c][w] == 0);
3648
3649 if (bp != NULL && !BP_IS_EMBEDDED(bp)) {
3650 ASSERT(bp->blk_pad[0] == 0);
3651 ASSERT(bp->blk_pad[1] == 0);
3652 ASSERT(bcmp(bp, &zio->io_bp_copy, sizeof (blkptr_t)) == 0 ||
3653 (bp == zio_unique_parent(zio)->io_bp));
3654 if (zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_WRITE && !BP_IS_HOLE(bp) &&
3655 zio->io_bp_override == NULL &&
3656 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_IO_REPAIR)) {
3657 ASSERT(!BP_SHOULD_BYTESWAP(bp));
3658 ASSERT3U(zio->io_prop.zp_copies, <=, BP_GET_NDVAS(bp));
3659 ASSERT(BP_COUNT_GANG(bp) == 0 ||
3660 (BP_COUNT_GANG(bp) == BP_GET_NDVAS(bp)));
3661 }
3662 if (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE)
3663 VERIFY(BP_EQUAL(bp, &zio->io_bp_orig));
3664 }
3665
3666 /*
3667 * If there were child vdev/gang/ddt errors, they apply to us now.
3668 */
3669 zio_inherit_child_errors(zio, ZIO_CHILD_VDEV);
3670 zio_inherit_child_errors(zio, ZIO_CHILD_GANG);
3671 zio_inherit_child_errors(zio, ZIO_CHILD_DDT);
3672
3673 /*
3674 * If the I/O on the transformed data was successful, generate any
3675 * checksum reports now while we still have the transformed data.
3676 */
3677 if (zio->io_error == 0) {
3678 while (zio->io_cksum_report != NULL) {
3679 zio_cksum_report_t *zcr = zio->io_cksum_report;
3680 uint64_t align = zcr->zcr_align;
3681 uint64_t asize = P2ROUNDUP(psize, align);
3682 char *abuf = zio->io_data;
3683
3684 if (asize != psize) {
3685 abuf = zio_buf_alloc(asize);
3686 bcopy(zio->io_data, abuf, psize);
3687 bzero(abuf + psize, asize - psize);
3688 }
3689
3690 zio->io_cksum_report = zcr->zcr_next;
3691 zcr->zcr_next = NULL;
3692 zcr->zcr_finish(zcr, abuf);
3693 zfs_ereport_free_checksum(zcr);
3694
3695 if (asize != psize)
3696 zio_buf_free(abuf, asize);
3697 }
3698 }
3699
3700 zio_pop_transforms(zio); /* note: may set zio->io_error */
3701
3702 vdev_stat_update(zio, psize);
3703
3704 if (zio->io_error) {
3705 /*
3706 * If this I/O is attached to a particular vdev,
3707 * generate an error message describing the I/O failure
3708 * at the block level. We ignore these errors if the
3709 * device is currently unavailable.
3710 */
3711 if (zio->io_error != ECKSUM && vd != NULL && !vdev_is_dead(vd))
3712 zfs_ereport_post(FM_EREPORT_ZFS_IO, spa, vd, zio, 0, 0);
3713
3714 if ((zio->io_error == EIO || !(zio->io_flags &
3715 (ZIO_FLAG_SPECULATIVE | ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE))) &&
3716 zio == lio) {
3717 /*
3718 * For logical I/O requests, tell the SPA to log the
3719 * error and generate a logical data ereport.
3720 */
3721 spa_log_error(spa, zio);
3722 zfs_ereport_post(FM_EREPORT_ZFS_DATA, spa, NULL, zio,
3723 0, 0);
3724 }
3725 }
3726
3727 if (zio->io_error && zio == lio) {
3728 /*
3729 * Determine whether zio should be reexecuted. This will
3730 * propagate all the way to the root via zio_notify_parent().
3731 */
3732 ASSERT(vd == NULL && bp != NULL);
3733 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
3734
3735 if (IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio) &&
3736 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL)) {
3737 if (zio->io_error != ENOSPC)
3738 zio->io_reexecute |= ZIO_REEXECUTE_NOW;
3739 else
3740 zio->io_reexecute |= ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND;
3741 }
3742
3743 if ((zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_READ ||
3744 zio->io_type == ZIO_TYPE_FREE) &&
3745 !(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_SCAN_THREAD) &&
3746 zio->io_error == ENXIO &&
3747 spa_load_state(spa) == SPA_LOAD_NONE &&
3748 spa_get_failmode(spa) != ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_CONTINUE)
3749 zio->io_reexecute |= ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND;
3750
3751 if (!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL) && !zio->io_reexecute)
3752 zio->io_reexecute |= ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND;
3753
3754 /*
3755 * Here is a possibly good place to attempt to do
3756 * either combinatorial reconstruction or error correction
3757 * based on checksums. It also might be a good place
3758 * to send out preliminary ereports before we suspend
3759 * processing.
3760 */
3761 }
3762
3763 /*
3764 * If there were logical child errors, they apply to us now.
3765 * We defer this until now to avoid conflating logical child
3766 * errors with errors that happened to the zio itself when
3767 * updating vdev stats and reporting FMA events above.
3768 */
3769 zio_inherit_child_errors(zio, ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
3770
3771 if ((zio->io_error || zio->io_reexecute) &&
3772 IO_IS_ALLOCATING(zio) && zio->io_gang_leader == zio &&
3773 !(zio->io_flags & (ZIO_FLAG_IO_REWRITE | ZIO_FLAG_NOPWRITE)))
3774 zio_dva_unallocate(zio, zio->io_gang_tree, bp);
3775
3776 zio_gang_tree_free(&zio->io_gang_tree);
3777
3778 /*
3779 * Godfather I/Os should never suspend.
3780 */
3781 if ((zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER) &&
3782 (zio->io_reexecute & ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND))
3783 zio->io_reexecute = 0;
3784
3785 if (zio->io_reexecute) {
3786 /*
3787 * This is a logical I/O that wants to reexecute.
3788 *
3789 * Reexecute is top-down. When an i/o fails, if it's not
3790 * the root, it simply notifies its parent and sticks around.
3791 * The parent, seeing that it still has children in zio_done(),
3792 * does the same. This percolates all the way up to the root.
3793 * The root i/o will reexecute or suspend the entire tree.
3794 *
3795 * This approach ensures that zio_reexecute() honors
3796 * all the original i/o dependency relationships, e.g.
3797 * parents not executing until children are ready.
3798 */
3799 ASSERT(zio->io_child_type == ZIO_CHILD_LOGICAL);
3800
3801 zio->io_gang_leader = NULL;
3802
3803 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
3804 zio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_DONE] = 1;
3805 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
3806
3807 /*
3808 * "The Godfather" I/O monitors its children but is
3809 * not a true parent to them. It will track them through
3810 * the pipeline but severs its ties whenever they get into
3811 * trouble (e.g. suspended). This allows "The Godfather"
3812 * I/O to return status without blocking.
3813 */
3814 zl = NULL;
3815 for (pio = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl); pio != NULL;
3816 pio = pio_next) {
3817 zio_link_t *remove_zl = zl;
3818 pio_next = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl);
3819
3820 if ((pio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER) &&
3821 (zio->io_reexecute & ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND)) {
3822 zio_remove_child(pio, zio, remove_zl);
3823 zio_notify_parent(pio, zio, ZIO_WAIT_DONE);
3824 }
3825 }
3826
3827 if ((pio = zio_unique_parent(zio)) != NULL) {
3828 /*
3829 * We're not a root i/o, so there's nothing to do
3830 * but notify our parent. Don't propagate errors
3831 * upward since we haven't permanently failed yet.
3832 */
3833 ASSERT(!(zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_GODFATHER));
3834 zio->io_flags |= ZIO_FLAG_DONT_PROPAGATE;
3835 zio_notify_parent(pio, zio, ZIO_WAIT_DONE);
3836 } else if (zio->io_reexecute & ZIO_REEXECUTE_SUSPEND) {
3837 /*
3838 * We'd fail again if we reexecuted now, so suspend
3839 * until conditions improve (e.g. device comes online).
3840 */
3841 zio_suspend(spa, zio);
3842 } else {
3843 /*
3844 * Reexecution is potentially a huge amount of work.
3845 * Hand it off to the otherwise-unused claim taskq.
3846 */
3847#if defined(illumos) || !defined(_KERNEL)
3848 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_next == NULL);
3849#elif defined(__NetBSD__)
3850 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_queued == 0);
3851#else
3852 ASSERT(zio->io_tqent.tqent_task.ta_pending == 0);
3853#endif
3854 spa_taskq_dispatch_ent(spa, ZIO_TYPE_CLAIM,
3855 ZIO_TASKQ_ISSUE, (task_func_t *)zio_reexecute, zio,
3856 0, &zio->io_tqent);
3857 }
3858 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3859 }
3860
3861 ASSERT(zio->io_child_count == 0);
3862 ASSERT(zio->io_reexecute == 0);
3863 ASSERT(zio->io_error == 0 || (zio->io_flags & ZIO_FLAG_CANFAIL));
3864
3865 /*
3866 * Report any checksum errors, since the I/O is complete.
3867 */
3868 while (zio->io_cksum_report != NULL) {
3869 zio_cksum_report_t *zcr = zio->io_cksum_report;
3870 zio->io_cksum_report = zcr->zcr_next;
3871 zcr->zcr_next = NULL;
3872 zcr->zcr_finish(zcr, NULL);
3873 zfs_ereport_free_checksum(zcr);
3874 }
3875
3876 /*
3877 * It is the responsibility of the done callback to ensure that this
3878 * particular zio is no longer discoverable for adoption, and as
3879 * such, cannot acquire any new parents.
3880 */
3881 if (zio->io_done)
3882 zio->io_done(zio);
3883
3884 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
3885 zio->io_state[ZIO_WAIT_DONE] = 1;
3886 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
3887
3888 zl = NULL;
3889 for (pio = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl); pio != NULL; pio = pio_next) {
3890 zio_link_t *remove_zl = zl;
3891 pio_next = zio_walk_parents(zio, &zl);
3892 zio_remove_child(pio, zio, remove_zl);
3893 zio_notify_parent(pio, zio, ZIO_WAIT_DONE);
3894 }
3895
3896 if (zio->io_waiter != NULL) {
3897 mutex_enter(&zio->io_lock);
3898 zio->io_executor = NULL;
3899 cv_broadcast(&zio->io_cv);
3900 mutex_exit(&zio->io_lock);
3901 } else {
3902 zio_destroy(zio);
3903 }
3904
3905 return (ZIO_PIPELINE_STOP);
3906}

3942
3943/*
3944 * Compare two zbookmark_phys_t's to see which we would reach first in a
3945 * pre-order traversal of the object tree.
3946 *
3947 * This is simple in every case aside from the meta-dnode object. For all other
3948 * objects, we traverse them in order (object 1 before object 2, and so on).
3949 * However, all of these objects are traversed while traversing object 0, since
3950 * the data it points to is the list of objects. Thus, we need to convert to a
3951 * canonical representation so we can compare meta-dnode bookmarks to
3952 * non-meta-dnode bookmarks.
3953 *
3954 * We do this by calculating "equivalents" for each field of the zbookmark.
3955 * zbookmarks outside of the meta-dnode use their own object and level, and
3956 * calculate the level 0 equivalent (the first L0 blkid that is contained in the
3957 * blocks this bookmark refers to) by multiplying their blkid by their span
3958 * (the number of L0 blocks contained within one block at their level).
3959 * zbookmarks inside the meta-dnode calculate their object equivalent
3960 * (which is L0equiv * dnodes per data block), use 0 for their L0equiv, and use
3961 * level + 1<<31 (any value larger than a level could ever be) for their level.
3962 * This causes them to always compare before a bookmark in their object
3963 * equivalent, compare appropriately to bookmarks in other objects, and to
3964 * compare appropriately to other bookmarks in the meta-dnode.
3965 */
3966int
3967zbookmark_compare(uint16_t dbss1, uint8_t ibs1, uint16_t dbss2, uint8_t ibs2,
3968 const zbookmark_phys_t *zb1, const zbookmark_phys_t *zb2)
3969{
3970 /*
3971 * These variables represent the "equivalent" values for the zbookmark,
3972 * after converting zbookmarks inside the meta dnode to their
3973 * normal-object equivalents.
3974 */
3975 uint64_t zb1obj, zb2obj;
3976 uint64_t zb1L0, zb2L0;
3977 uint64_t zb1level, zb2level;
3978
3979 if (zb1->zb_object == zb2->zb_object &&
3980 zb1->zb_level == zb2->zb_level &&
3981 zb1->zb_blkid == zb2->zb_blkid)
3982 return (0);
3983
3984 /*
3985 * BP_SPANB calculates the span in blocks.
3986 */
3987 zb1L0 = (zb1->zb_blkid) * BP_SPANB(ibs1, zb1->zb_level);
3988 zb2L0 = (zb2->zb_blkid) * BP_SPANB(ibs2, zb2->zb_level);
3989
3990 if (zb1->zb_object == DMU_META_DNODE_OBJECT) {
3991 zb1obj = zb1L0 * (dbss1 << (SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT - DNODE_SHIFT));
3992 zb1L0 = 0;
3993 zb1level = zb1->zb_level + COMPARE_META_LEVEL;
3994 } else {
3995 zb1obj = zb1->zb_object;
3996 zb1level = zb1->zb_level;
3997 }
3998
3999 if (zb2->zb_object == DMU_META_DNODE_OBJECT) {
4000 zb2obj = zb2L0 * (dbss2 << (SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT - DNODE_SHIFT));
4001 zb2L0 = 0;
4002 zb2level = zb2->zb_level + COMPARE_META_LEVEL;
4003 } else {
4004 zb2obj = zb2->zb_object;
4005 zb2level = zb2->zb_level;
4006 }
4007
4008 /* Now that we have a canonical representation, do the comparison. */
4009 if (zb1obj != zb2obj)
4010 return (zb1obj < zb2obj ? -1 : 1);
4011 else if (zb1L0 != zb2L0)
4012 return (zb1L0 < zb2L0 ? -1 : 1);
4013 else if (zb1level != zb2level)
4014 return (zb1level > zb2level ? -1 : 1);
4015 /*
4016 * This can (theoretically) happen if the bookmarks have the same object
4017 * and level, but different blkids, if the block sizes are not the same.
4018 * There is presently no way to change the indirect block sizes
4019 */
4020 return (0);
4021}
4022
4023/*
4024 * This function checks the following: given that last_block is the place that
4025 * our traversal stopped last time, does that guarantee that we've visited
4026 * every node under subtree_root? Therefore, we can't just use the raw output
4027 * of zbookmark_compare. We have to pass in a modified version of
4028 * subtree_root; by incrementing the block id, and then checking whether
4029 * last_block is before or equal to that, we can tell whether or not having
4030 * visited last_block implies that all of subtree_root's children have been
4031 * visited.
4032 */
4033boolean_t
4034zbookmark_subtree_completed(const dnode_phys_t *dnp,
4035 const zbookmark_phys_t *subtree_root, const zbookmark_phys_t *last_block)
4036{
4037 zbookmark_phys_t mod_zb = *subtree_root;
4038 mod_zb.zb_blkid++;
4039 ASSERT(last_block->zb_level == 0);
4040
4041 /* The objset_phys_t isn't before anything. */
4042 if (dnp == NULL)
4043 return (B_FALSE);
4044
4045 /*
4046 * We pass in 1ULL << (DNODE_BLOCK_SHIFT - SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT) for the
4047 * data block size in sectors, because that variable is only used if
4048 * the bookmark refers to a block in the meta-dnode. Since we don't
4049 * know without examining it what object it refers to, and there's no
4050 * harm in passing in this value in other cases, we always pass it in.
4051 *
4052 * We pass in 0 for the indirect block size shift because zb2 must be
4053 * level 0. The indirect block size is only used to calculate the span
4054 * of the bookmark, but since the bookmark must be level 0, the span is
4055 * always 1, so the math works out.
4056 *
4057 * If you make changes to how the zbookmark_compare code works, be sure
4058 * to make sure that this code still works afterwards.
4059 */
4060 return (zbookmark_compare(dnp->dn_datablkszsec, dnp->dn_indblkshift,
4061 1ULL << (DNODE_BLOCK_SHIFT - SPA_MINBLOCKSHIFT), 0, &mod_zb,
4062 last_block) <= 0);
4063}
